<HEAD><TITLE>
About SUNY Potsdam and the GLC
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<h4><center>About Us</center></h4>
<CENTER><TABLE border=2 CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>
 <tr align=center>
<td>
<IMG Width= 170 Align=Top SRC="TE.gif">
</td>
</tr>
</table></CENTER>
<H4>About SUNY Potsdam</A></H4>
<FONT SIZE=2>	Founded in 1816, SUNY Potsdam is the oldest campus of the State University of New York and has a long history of Teacher Education and Liberal Arts.  Approximately 4000 undergraduate and 600 graduate students are enrolled in the  schools Music, Liberal Studies, and Education.  Undergraduate students pursue  a Bachelor of Arts degree in a major of their choice, and may elect either to co major in Education at the undergraduate level, or wait until they have completed their B.A. before entering the Master of Science in Teaching program.  Innovative  Math, Science, and Technology teacher education programs has been supported at SUNY Potsdam by the  National Science Foundation and the Eisenhower Program for Science and Mathematics.<p>
Located 60 miles north of Lake Placid N.Y. and 80 miles south of Ottawa Canada, SUNY Potsdam is one of 4 colleges in the Associated Colleges of Northern New York, with a combined enrollement of 11,000 undergraduate students in the towns of Potsdam and Canton. </FONT> <p>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=2>Comments on the contents of these pages may be sent to:</FONT></CENTER> <BR>
<a href=mailto:doodywj@potsdam.edu><FONT SIZE=2>Bill Doody</a>, Ph.D., Science Education</FONT> ; or 
<a href=mailto:smithbs@potsdam.edu><FONT SIZE=2>Bev Smith</a>, Math Education;  or</FONT> 
<a href=mailto:sipherjd@potsdam.edu><FONT SIZE=2>Justin Sipher</a>, Distributed Computing.</FONT><P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=2>        Home </FONT><A HREF="home.html"><IMG WIDTH=33 Align=Top SRC="besthome.gif"></A></CENTER>
</CENTER>
