<HEAD><TITLE>MRSI: Municipal Garage Sale, Sept. 1996</TITLE></HEAD> 

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER><IMG Align=Center SRC="logo-red.GIF"><BR>
<BR>
 <H1>William C. Merwin <BR>
Rural Services Institute</CENTER></H1> <br>
<IMG  WIDTH=150  HEIGHT=100  Align=Left SRC="mgs.gif">

<H2>Municipal Garage Sale Directory<BR>
September, 1996<BR>
Volume 2, No. 2</H2>

<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR WIDTH=100%><P>
<BR>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>A Directory of items for sale, exchange, rent or trade among local governments in the North Country
</H3><P>
<FONT SIZE=4>
The Municipal Garage Sale (MGS) directory is a compilation of items for sale, exchange, or trade among local governments in Franklin, Jefferson, Lewis and St. Lawrence Counties in Northern New York.  This directory provides a forum for the information exchange necessary for local governments to acquire or dispose of surplus equipment, supplies or other valuable items.  This dedicated channel for resource exchange assists all local governments to operate more efficiently.<P>

Please read through the ads; if you are interested in an item, call the designated contact person for further information and to make arrangements to acquire the item(s).<P>
<PRE><A HREF="sale.html">For Sale Ads</A>	<!-- Link Tag -->	   <A HREF="wanted.html">Wanted Ads</A>	<!-- Link Tag -->	   <A HREF="Give.html">Give Away Ads</A>	

</PRE>
Please take a moment to fill out our Municipal Garage Sale <!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.potsdam.edu/MRSI/MGS_Sep96/survey.html">customer survey</A>.  We would like to track how helpful this directory is for local government officials.<P>

If you would like to place an ad in the next MGS directory, to be published in March 1997, go to "place an ad" below and follow instructions.<P>
<CENTER><A HREF="place.html">Place an Ad</A></CENTER><P>
<BR>

The Municipal Garage Sale directory is published by the William C. Merwin Rural Services Institute of SUNY Potsdam with the guidance of the Local Government Planning Group. <P>
The Local Government Planning Group  includes:<P>
<FONT SIZE=3>
 <B>Ruth Garner</B>, Mayor, Village of Potsdam and Chair of the Advisory Board  <BR>
<B>Frank Alguire</B>, Executive Director, Massena Economic Development Council  <BR>
<B>Roselie Bambrey</B>, Director, Potsdam Economic Development Zone <BR>
<B> Duana Carey</B>, St. Lawrence County Legislator <BR>
<B> Ram Chugh</B>, Director, William C. Merwin  Rural Services Institute <BR>
 <B>Joseph Gray</B>, Private Consultant<BR>
  <B>Duane Hazelton</B>, Supervisor, Town of Massena <BR>
 <B>Dean Lefebvre</B>, Supervisor, Town of Altamont<BR>
  <B>Donald McIntyre</B>, Supervisor, Town of Westport <BR>
 <B>Richard Mooers</B>, Director, St. Lawrence County Planning Office <BR>
 <B>June F. O'Neill</B>, Executive Coordinator for Training and Intergovernmental Affairs, NYS Comptroller's Office <BR>
 <B>Richard Reno</B>, St. Lawrence County Superintendent of Highways <BR>
<B> Nick Russell</B>, Economic Development Coordinator, St. Regis Mohawk Tribe  <BR>
<B>Margaret Stacy</B>, Town Clerk, Town of Canton<BR>
 <B> Michael Weil</B>, Administrator, Village of Potsdam<P>
</FONT>
</FONT>
 The Municipal Garage Sale directory was produced by John F. Tenbusch and William J. Stack of the Merwin Rural Services Institute, with  greatly appreciated help from the Office of College Relations. <P>


<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
