<BR>
<FONT SIZE=5><B><CENTER><!-- Anchor Point Tag --><A NAME="MetraHealth Zip Code Change">MetraHealth Zip Code Change</A>
</CENTER></B></FONT>
<BR>
The Kingston Post Office has advised MetraHealth that their zip code is
being changed from 12401-0600 to 12402-1600.  The post office box number is
now incorporated into the zip code.  MetraHealth is now having its claimfor
ms reprinted using the new zip code.  Please use the new zip code beginning
immediately.<BR>

<BR>
<HR>
<BR>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=5><B><CENTER><!-- Anchor Point Tag -->
<A NAME="Tax Sheltered Annuities">Increase Your Retirement Savings through
Tax Sheltered Annuities</A></CENTER></B></FONT>

<BR>
<FONT SIZE=4>It makes good sense to put aside some extra savings for
retirement and the beginning of the tax year is a good time to start!  One
of the best ways to do it is through tax sheltered annuities.  All
full-time employees and most part-time employees are eligible to
participate in these before tax savings programs.  Classified employees may
only participate in <B>Tax Deferred Annuity Programs (TDAs)</B> offered by
TIAA-CREF or <I>the Copeland Companies</I>.  Accumulations in these savings
accounts are non-cashable and must be taken out in an annuity.
Unclassified service employees are eligible for <B>Supplemental Retirement
Annuity Programs (SRAs)</B> offered by TIAA-CREF or through <I>Aetna</I>.
SRAs are fully cashable, except there may be penalties before age 59-1/2.
Although there is a maximum exclusion allowance you cannot exceed in each
tax year, employees may choose to participate for as little as $5.00 per
pay period.</FONT><BR>
<BR>
<HR>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=5><B><CENTER><!-- Anchor Point Tag -->
<A NAME="Social Security and Medicare 1996">Social Security and Medicare
Deductions for 1997</A></CENTER></B></FONT>

<BR>
<FONT SIZE=4>The 1997 Social Security tax will be calculated at 6.2% on the first $65,400 of wages resulting in a maximum Social Security tax deduction of $4,054.80.  The $1.45% Medicare tax will apply to all taxable wages as there is no wage cap.
</FONT><BR>
<BR>
<BR>

