<FONT SIZE=5><B><CENTER><!-- Anchor Point Tag -->
<A NAME="Disability Insurance">Disability Insurance</A></CENTER></B></FONT><BR>

<FONT SIZE=4>There is no disability insurance for classified service employees beyond sick leave and other accruals plus, with some restrictions, one pay period at half pay for each six months of service.  For full-time and part-time unclassified service employees meeting salary or course load eligibility requirements, the following plan, fully funded by the University, is provided:</FONT>

<FONT SIZE=4><BLOCKQUOTE>Coverage after one year of employment.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>Benefits begin 6 months after commencement of disability.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>60% of monthly salary not to exceed $5,000 per month (inclusive of social security disability benefits, workers' compensation, the University's sick leave program and any pension benefits payable under the New York State Teachers' or New York State Employee's retirement systems).</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>Monthly TIAA annuity premium benefit equal to 12% of the first $1,375 of covered monthly salary plus 15% of covered monthly salary in excess of $1,375 is payable until disability ceases or age 65.  Annuity benefit applies to members of ERS and TRS retirement systems as well as participants in SUNY's ORP.</BLOCKQUOTE></FONT><BR>
<BR>
