<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Payroll</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 

<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=119  NAME="SUNY Potsdam - Human Resources" SRC="HR.gif"><BR>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=4><B><CENTER>PAYROLL</CENTER></B><BR>
<BR>



<FONT SIZE=5><CENTER><B><!-- Anchor Point Tag --><A NAME="Attendance and Leave">Attendance and Leave</A></FONT></B></CENTER><BR>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=5><CENTER><B><!-- Anchor Point Tag -->
<A NAME="Holidays 1996">New York State Holidays 1996</A></B></CENTER></FONT><BR>
<BR>
Classified service employees who are required to work on holidays either: (1) receive holiday pay (pay for an extra day at straight time rate), or (2) accrue a day off if they have filed a holiday pay waiver with Human Resources.  Professional staff with either college year or calendar year obligations who are required to work on holidays accrue a compensatory day off.  Part-time employees are eligible to accrue only holidays that fall on their normal day of work.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR WIDTH=60% SIZE=5 ALIGN=Center>
<BR>
<BR>
<B>DR. MARTIN LUTHER KING, JR. DAY, Monday, January 15, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>No classes scheduled.  Most administrative offices closed.  Staffing should be limited to providing essential services.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>LINCOLN'S BIRTHDAY, Monday, February 12, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Classes in session.  Normal operations.  Lincoln's Birthday has been designated as a floating holiday for employees in the CSEA, PEF, UUP bargaining units and for Managerial/Confidential employees.  Employees in the above units must use the floating holiday within one year for a full day absence.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>WASHINGTON'S BIRTHDAY, Monday, February 19, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>No classes scheduled.  Most administrative offices closed.  Staffing should be limited to providing essential services.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>MEMORIAL DAY, Monday, May 27, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>No classes scheduled.  The College will be officially closed.  Staffing should be limited to providing essential services.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>INDEPENDENCE DAY, Thursday, July 4, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>No classes scheduled.  The College will be officially closed and only essential public safety and physical plant operations will be maintained.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>The College requests that supervisors provide a liberal leave policy for employees on Friday, July 5, 1996.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>LABOR DAY, Monday, September 2, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Classes will be in session.  Some administrative offices closed.  Staffing should be limited to providing essential services.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>COLUMBUS DAY, Monday, October 14, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>No classes scheduled.  Staffing should be limited to providing essential services.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>ELECTION DAY, Tuesday, November 5, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Classes will be in session.  Normal operations.  Election Day has been designated as a floating holiday for employees in CSEA, PEF, M/C bargaining units and for UUP employees with college year or calendar year obligations.  The Friday after Thanksgiving is the designated floating holiday for UUP employees.  Other employees must use the floating holiday within one year for a full day absence.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>VETERANS' DAY, Monday, November 11, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Classes will be in session.  Some administrative offices closed.  Staffing should be limited to providing essential services.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>THANKSGIVING DAY, Thursday, November 28, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>The College will be officially closed and only essential public safety and physical plant operations will be maintained. </BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>The College requests that supervisors provide a liberal leave policy for employees on Friday, November 29, 1996.  The names of employees not choosing leave on November 29, 1996, must be submitted to Human Resources by the close of business on Friday, November 22, 1996.  Human Resources will notify such employees of their alternative work location for this day.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<B>CHRISTMAS DAY, Wednesday, December 25, 1996</B><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>The College will be officially closed and only essential public safety and physical plant operations will be maintained.</BLOCKQUOTE>


