<CENTER><B><!-- Anchor Point Tag --><A NAME="NYS ERS"><!-- Font Tag --><!--
Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4><B>New York State Employees' Retirement
System</B></FONT></A><BR></B>
Governor Smith State Office Building<BR>
Albany, NY  12244</CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<B>Telephone Numbers</B><BR>
1-518-474-7736........membership questions<BR>
1-518-473-1355........loan information<BR>

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<B>Representatives Available</B><BR>
You may meet with a NYSERS representative on the first Thursday of each
month from 9 am - noon and from 1 pm - 4 pm in Room 117B, French Hall, at
SUNY Canton.  There are no appointments, meetings are held on a first-come,
first-served basis.<BR><BR>
Other locations that are open from 9 am - 4 pm:<BR>
Plattsburgh, County Center, 137 Margaret Street ---------- Third Thursday<BR>
Syracuse, County Courthouse, 401 Montgomery Street ---------- Second & Fourth Friday<BR>
Watertown, Jefferson County Human Services Building, 250 Arsenal St ---------- First Friday
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=45% SIZE=3 ALIGN=Center NOSHADE>
<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><!-- Anchor Point Tag --><A NAME="NYS TRS"><B><!-- Font Tag
--><FONT SIZE=4>New York State Teachers' Retirement
System</FONT></B></A><BR>
10 Corporate Woods Drive<BR>
Albany, NY  12211-2395<BR></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<B>Telephone Numbers</B><BR>
1-800-348-7298......General information/membership questions<BR>


<BR>
<BR>
<B>Representatives Available</B><BR>
Confidential interviews between members and System representatives are
conducted on the dates indicated below.  This is a partial listing.  For
other locations and dates, please contact Human Resources.  Appointments
are made ONLY by calling the phone numbers shown.  To make an appointment,
call the number of the consultation site of your choice and give your name
and home telephone number.  Since the person taking your call is not an
employee of the Retirement System, please save your questions for the
System representtive at your interview.  For your comprehensive retirement
planning, System representatives are equipped with personal computers and
portable printers to provide on-the-spot, hard-copy estimates for
discussion during your consultation.  These estimates, computed via phone
line to System offices in Albany, may be generated using variables such as:
different retirement dates, termination pay, fixed income protection for a
beneficiry and withdrawal of member contributions. <BR>

You need to bring with you
<BLOCKQUOTE>*your latest Member Annual Statement issued by the Retirement
System, <BR>
*salary information by school year (7/1 - 6/30) for the last year, current
and future years, and <BR>
*amount of termination pay, retirement bonus or pay for unused sick days or
accumulated vacation.</BLOCKQUOTE>
Albany, NYS Teachers' Retirement System, 10 Corporate Woods Dr.<BR>
1-800-348-7298 [ext 6100]<BR>
Appointments are scheduled during regular business hours (M-F)<BR>


Plattsburgh, Plattsburgh High School, 1 Clifford Dr, Suite 102<BR>
Call 518-561-7500<BR>
Dates  TBD<BR>
<BR>

Potsdam, Potsdam Central School, 29 Leroy Street  <BR>
Call 315-265-2000 [ext 212]<BR>
Dates  TBD<BR>
<BR>

Saranac Lake, Middle School, Petrova Ave  <BR>
Call 518-891-4221<BR>
Dates  TBD<BR>
<BR>

Watertown, Watertown High School, 1335 Washington St  <BR>
Call 315-785-3812<BR>
DATES   TBD<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<B>Statewide Pre-Retirement Planning Seminars</B>
<BR>
The New York State Teachers' Retirement System schedules a series of
Statewide Pre-retirement Planning Seminars.  The day-long (8 am - 4 pm)
seminars will feature presentations by various professionals and will also
include discussions on financial planning, social security, adjusting to
retirement, legal considerations, Retirement System benefits, retirement
incentives and other retirement related topics.  The purpose of the program is to
focus attention on the questions and concerns which are important to those
preparing for retirement.  The seminars are open to active members of TRS
age 45 and older.  Reservations will be taken on a first call basis.
Spouses are also invited and encouraged to attend.  Since seminar
participants are provided with personalized benefit information, they
should be prepared to show photo identification at the seminar.  Cost per
member is $10, while the fee per non-member spouse is $5.  To secure a
reservation, please telephone 1-800-356-3128 (ext 6180).  Telephone
reservations can ONLY be made by calling this number between 8:30 am and
4:15 pm.  When calling, please provide your membership number and/or social
security number, date of birth, home address, home and work telephone
numbers and indicate if your spouse is attending.  If your spouse is a
member, please have the above information for him/her also.  For admittance into the seminar, please be prepared to show photo identification.  For other
locations and dates, please contact Human Resources.
<BR>
<BR>

BUFFALO<BR>
Sheraton Inn, 2040 Walden Avenue<BR>
TBD<BR>
<BR>


SYRACUSE<BR>
Four Points by Sheraton, 7th No. St. & Electronics Pkwy, Exit 37 NYS Thruway<BR>
TBD<BR>
