REFERENCE/SCIENCE LIBRARIAN:  The State University of New York College at Potsdam, Frederick W. Crumb Memorial Library, invites applications for a librarian at the assistant or senior assistant level.  This is a permanent, 12-month position with faculty status.  Librarians are eligible for continuing appointment.  Responsibilities:  Reference and Information services with some evening and weekend reference desk coverage; collection development responsibilities; participation in the library's instruction program and serve as faculty liaison for assigned areas.  Qualifications:  MLS is required from an ALA accredited program; degree or significant course work in the natural sciences; strong academic background; familiarity with electronic information resources and automated library systems; superior verbal and written communication skills and a willingness to work in a team environment.  Preferred qualification:  second Master's in a natural science discipline.  The Libraries utilize a range of technological applications including an integrated on-line system (multiLIS), networked stations for CD-ROM searching, public access to the Internet and a web site that is part of the college's WWW service.  Send letter of application, resume and the names, addresses and telephone numbers of three references to:  Nancy Alzo, Chair, Search Committee, Crumb Library, SUNY Potsdam, Potsdam, NY 13676.  Application deadline is November 15, 1996.  State University of New York College at Potsdam is an equal opportunity affirmative action employer committed to excellence through diversity.


