SUNY Potsdam invites applications for a temporary one-year position at the rank of instructor or assistant professor of Employee Relations beginning September 1997.  (The successful candidate will be eligible to apply for the tenure-track position which will be advertised during the 1997-98 academic year.)  Requirements:  Ph.D. or ABD in the final stage of dissertation writing; for appointment at the assistant professor level, applicants must hold the Ph.D. by date of appointment.  Salary is $30,000 for assistant, $28,000 for instructor.  Four courses per semester; excellence in teaching and commitment to continued professional development through scholarship are vital to the position.  The candidate is expected to teach Employment Law, Labor Law, Collective Bargaining, and other employee relations courses.  Applications will be accepted until March 21, 1997.  For full consideration, send a cover letter indicating your previous teaching experience and describing your teaching methods or approaches; curriculum vitae; copy of graduate transcript; teaching evaluations; and three letters of reference to:  Professor Paul Baktari, Chair, Department of Economics, SUNY Potsdam, Potsdam, NY 13676.  State University of New York at Potsdam is an equal opportunity affirmative action employer committed to excellence through diversity.
