<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>MRSI: A.C. Walker Foundation</TITLE></HEAD> 
<!-- Body Tag -->
<BODY BACKGROUND="yellow.jpg">
</BODY>

<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=32 HEIGHT=32 ALIGN=center SRC="logo-red.GIF"></CENTER><P>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>William C. Merwin <BR>
Rural Services Institute</H1><P>
<HR WIDTH=100%><P>
<CENTER><font color='000873'><FONT SIZE=6>A.C. W</FONT><FONT SIZE=5>ALKER </FONT><FONT SIZE=6>F</FONT><FONT SIZE=5>OUNDATION</FONT></CENTER>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=6>N</FONT><FONT SIZE=5>ORTH </FONT><FONT SIZE=6>C</FONT><FONT SIZE=5>OUNTRY </FONT><FONT SIZE=6>R</FONT><FONT SIZE=5>ESEARCH </FONT><FONT SIZE=6>F</FONT><FONT SIZE=5>ELLOWSHIPS</FONT></CENTER></font><P>


<FONT SIZE=4> 
The A.C. Walker Foundation is seeking applications for its 1996-97 North Country Research Fellowships, for faculty at colleges in Clinton, Essex, Franklin, Jefferson, Lewis, and St. Lawrence counties.  The fellowships, administered by the William C. Merwin Rural Services Institute (MRSI) at SUNY Potsdam and ranging from $2,000 to $8,000, are intended to encourage faculty to research critical problems confronting the region, including economic, social and educational problems.  In their fourth year of existence, the fellowships are designed to form partnerships between faculty and community "sponsors" from regional or local organizations and businesses.  <P>
<!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="guidelines.html">View Guidelines for Research Projects
</A><P>

The applications must be postmarked by March 7.  After they are evaluated by the Fellowships Advisory Council, the council's recommendations will be submitted to Interim President Jean A. Scott for the final decision.  The recipients will be notified in late April.  The advisory council may choose to award fellowships of under $2,000.  
<P>

To receive an application and <!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="guidelines.html">guidelines</A>, contact MRSI at (315) 267-2397 or by e-mail to <!-- MailTo Tag -->
<A HREF="MAILTO:tenbusjf@potsdam.edu">tenbusjf@potsdam.edu</A>.<P> 

You can see a list previous A.C. Walker Fellowship Research reports which have been published and are available from MRSI, at the <!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.potsdam.edu/mrsi/publications.html">MRSI Publications</A> page.
</font>
</BODY> 
</HTML> 
</DOC>
