<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Thanksgiving Lesson</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY Background="yellowbk.gif" Text=#5C3317">
<FONT SIZE=4>


Benjamin B. Rudd<BR>
Lesson Plan - Our Thanksgiving Fun<BR>
<P><P>
Objectives:  The students will write a story about something fun that they do on Thanksgiving day and draw a picture that will match the story.
<P><P>
Materials:<BR>
		Pencils<BR>
		Crayons<BR>
		Thanksgiving sheets<BR>
<P><P>

Procedure:<BR>
	Model a story of your own with a picture to show the students how their stories will be generated.  Then, with the help of the students, create a rubric that will be used to evaluate their stories.  After having done so, the students will write their own stories and then show them to the teacher as they finish.  The teacher will review the stories with the students, guiding them through the revision and editing process.  After the teacher has approved the students work, the student will illustrate the story with a picture that will match it.  When all of the stories are complete, the teacher will use them to create a bulletin board for Thanksgiving.<BR><P><P>

Evaluation:<BR>
	The students will be graded on a scale of four, using the rubric that the students created as a basis for grading.<BR><P>

</BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
