<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Lesson Plan: Look At The Light</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY Background="redbkg.gif" TEXT="#FFFFFF">
<FONT SIZE=4>



Name: Jennifer Grifa<BR><P>
Type of Lesson: Science<BR><P>
Name of Lesson: Let's Look at Light<BR><P>
Lesson Concepts:<BR>
	-The students will understand the words about their light unit<BR>
	-The students will work together to share understanding of their words<BR><P><B>Lesson Skills:</B> <BR><P>	
<B>Reading</B><BR>
	-Working with a partner<BR>
	-Matching words to their definitions then to a visual cue<BR><P>
<B>Lesson Objectives and Outcomes:</B><BR>
	-The students will have matched up with the person who either has the definition to their word or the word that matches their definition.  Together they will place them underneath the appropriate picture on the bulletin board. (see pictures)<BR><P>
<B>Phase 1 (engagement, link) strategy:</B><BR>
	-The students will read a list of words and definitions aloud according to volunteers.  The definitions will have to do with the words that they will be using in their light unit.<BR><P>
<B>Phase2 (teach, distributed guided practice, reteach) strategy:</B><BR>
	-The students will be randomly passed either a definition card or a vocabulary card.  The students will then have to be matched up with a partner that goes along with the card that they have been given.  The students will have to talk and discuss what card they have with every students in order to find their partner. (see pictures)<P>
<B>Phase3 (closure, bridge) strategy:</B><BR>
	-After the students have paired up, they will go to the bulletin board (see pictures) and place their cards under the appropriate picture.  After everyone has done so correctly the bulletin board will be completed and it will prove as a reference source during the unit.<BR><P>
<B>Type of Assessment:</B><BR>
	-Correct matching up with your partner<BR>
	-Placing cards in the appropriate place on the bulletin board<BR>
	-Participation in class.<BR><P>
<B>Materials:</B><BR>
	-Bulletin Board<BR>
	-Vocabulary Cards<BR>
	-Definition Cards<BR>
	-Vocabulary Sheet<BR>
	-Picture Cards<BR>

</BODY></HTML>

