<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Chapter 4D</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<dt><br>
<CENTER><strong>IV.  FACULTY COMPENSATION</strong></CENTER> 
<BR>
<BR>

<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="4D"><strong>D</A>.	DUAL EMPLOYMENT</strong>
<dt><br>
In contrast to extra service, "dual employment" procedures are applicable when a State employee's combined employment (more than one appointment) with the State does not exceed one hundred percent (100%) of full-time.  Under such circumstances, payment in the secondary agency, i.e., the agency where the employee is to be employed subsequent to employment in another agency, may only be effected after the employee has obtained dual employment authorization from the primary employing agency.

</dl>
	<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
</dl>
</dl>
</dl>
<br><br>
