<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Chapter 4J</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><strong>IV.  FACULTY COMPENSATION</strong></CENTER> <BR>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><strong>J.	<!-- Anchor Point Tag --><A NAME="SUPPLEMENTAL RETIREMENT ANNUITY PROGRAM (SRA)">SUPPLEMENTAL RETIREMENT ANNUITY PROGRAM (SRA)</A> </strong>
<dt><br>
	The Supplemental Retirement Annuity Program (SRA) is another 403-b tax deferred program available to Managerial/Confidential (M/C) employees and employees represented by UUP.  Only TIAA/CREF issues contracts under this program.  Conditions of investment are the same as those defined in the Tax Deferred Annuity Program information.  One distinct feature which applies only to individuals enrolled in a Supplemental Retirement Annuity Program is related to the pay-out option.  SRA enrollees have a choice of a lump sum distribution or a monthly annuity at the time of retirement or upon reaching age 59 1/2.  There is no lump sum distribution available to enrollees in a TDA program.
<dt><br>
An employee enrolled in an SRA program through TIAA/CREF may, without penalty, roll over SRA accumulations to other recognized investment programs and receive the same tax deferred status of dollars rolled over.  Employees interested in the "roll over" provision should contact the various program representatives. 
<BR>
<BR>

<br>
