<TITLE>bioone.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H2>THE INCREDIBLE JOURNEY </H2>
 by Roger Dean<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Once a long time ago at the dawn of time,  a water drop was born named Jim. When Jim 
was born he lived in a lake, but when he was about 1,000 years old, he wished he 
could leave the lake.  All of the sudden, he started to float upwards!  He was evaporating.  Suddenly he found himself up in a cloud mixed with dirt and acid.  After about 
1 year, Jim was rudely awakened.   He woke as he was falling down towards the earth. 
  With a smack, he hit the ground!   He felt himself sinking into the ground. After 
 1 billion years, Jim was drank by a plant that was then knocked down by a big brontosaurus. 
 When the brontosaurus knocked over the plant, a triceratops ate it.  Jim was now 
stuck in the dinosaur.  After a few days out pops Jim on the ground. After that, 
Jim soaked into an underground water flow and then into a river.   After another billion 
years, he was floating in an ocean when he started  to get cool.  He started to freeze. 
After 3 billion years, he unfroze and was off again.   He was floating along peacefully when he was sucked up by a pioneer's mouth.   One day later, Jim was out on the 
ground again. Today, he is inside Roger Dean celebrating his birthday<BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="biotwo.html">Journal 2</A></H4>

</BODY>
</HTML>
