<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ritaone.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><CENTER><!-- Graphic Tag --><IMG WIDTH=214 HEIGHT=160  SRC="rita.gif"></CENTER>
<STRONG>Thursday, September 4th</STRONG>
<BR>
<BR>
This was the big day when we finally met the students we had been preparing for all 
summer. I surprised myself how comfortable I felt in front of the students. I was 
not nervous, just excited to finally start putting our lesson plans into action. 
There were times this summer when it seemed we were designing this grand scheme for no one, 
but now it is all coming together.<BR>
We initiated the day's lesson by playing a name game for an icebreaker. I had reservations 
about using this game as a starting point for our relationship with the students. 
I had used this game with college students when I was a residential assistant and 
it was horrible. Fortunately, the game is much better suited to 7th and 8th graders. 
The activity turned out to be not only helpful but enjoyable as well.<BR>
Once we finished the game, the students were given a brief introduction to the semesters 
anticipated projects and goals. The students all seemed very interested which was 
very encouraging. I noticed that the students seemed more nervous talking aloud to 
us than we did to them. I will be happy when the feelings of awkwardness disappear. 
I think it will make the students more willing to participate. <BR>
Overall, I was extremely pleased with todays experience. I am anxious to get started 
and hope their enthusiasm  and mine continues.<BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="ritatwo.html">Journal 2</A></H4>

</BODY>
</HTML>
