<TITLE>Sept.5 Donna [v4.0]</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Donna J. Derrigo-Graves<BR>
<BR>
9/5/96<BR>
<BR>
Met the kids for the first time today.  Although we were all excited we tried to get 
to know each other a little better.  We started with a name game.  Each person had 
to say their name and something they like to do that started with the same letter. 
 It was hard getting used to these kids calling me Mrs. Graves.  This seemed to unify 
the group slightly more than when we had started.  There were some obvious differences, 
though.<BR>
We separated the group into two informal groups and told them some information about 
the river.  We also gave them an interest survey so we could divide the group into 
two teams - Biology and Chemistry.  I was surprised at how hard the students worked 
on the surveys.  All in all it was a good day.
