<HEAD>
<TITLE>ritatwo.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<STRONG>Monday, September 9th</STRONG>
<BR>
<BR>
This was not a planned teaching day for me but I traveled to Gouverneur to morally 
support another Potsdam student who was not worked with the students yet and was 
really nervous about her first day. It was my first trip to the Gouverneur School 
 and so I felt a little awkward entering a public school to teach for the first time. <BR>
The plan of the day was to introduce the students to the factors pertaining to ecosystems. 
The goal was to prepare the students for the weeks lessons. Ms. Plemmons had planned 
to do this in the old fashioned lecture style that we are all so used to. It was boring for me, so I'm sure it was not stimulating for the kids. I brought in a few 
field guides and many different types of leaves to identify. I was really pleased 
with how the hands-on learning approach worked. It sure is easier to teach when the 
kids are motivated. Ms. Plemmons and I both decided that although some lecturing may be 
necessary that it is much more interesting to include activities for spice.<BR>
