<BODY>
Melissa Plemons<BR>
Monday September 16, 1996<BR>
Journal #2<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Today was my first day by myself.  Strangely enough, I wasn't as nervous as I was 
the week before.  It took a little while before the kids settled down, but after 
a few threats about taking away their Union privileges, they soon realized that I 
wasn't kidding and I really would.  So, they got to work!  I first read them a little excerpt 
and asked them to imagine as I read.  I was a little hesitant to do this activity 
at first because I thought they would fool around through it.  But, I was surprised 
to find that they did do it- maybe they didn't imagine as I read, but at least they didn't 
fool around through the entire thing.   <BR>
I really feel like I got a lot accomplished today.  The student's enjoyed drawing 
their poster even more than I thought they would, and they didn't moan and groan 
about presenting it in front of the class. I kept the posters, even though they all 
said they didn't want them, some of them were very creative and impressive.  The level of 
cooperative learning is still low, because I am assuming that they have never been 
introduced to it formally.  Being that today was my first time trying to implement 
it,I was surprised that it didn't result in disaster (like some people report it doing). 
 I ran out of time, and wasn't able to ask the students questions about cooperative 
learning that I had planned.  Mrs. Graves said that I could use the first 5-10 minutes 
of her class on Thursday to do that, and then I want to stick around to observe them 
working in groups.  <BR>
A few anectotal things I experienced was the kids reaction to my use of the word "flirt". 
 Some thought that I wasn't allowed to say that, while others were extremely verbal 
about their opinion that  I was the teacher and could do anything I wanted to.  Also, one of the students was pleased to find that he could make me laugh.  My question 
is, "Is it all right to laugh at the students, or not?"  <BR>
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="melisthr.html">Journal 3</A></CENTER>
</BODY>
