<TITLE>Sept.12 Donna [v4.0]</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Donna J. Derrigo-Graves<BR>
<BR>
9-12-96<BR>
<BR>
Today was the first day for me to actually teach alone.  We were in a very cramped 
room.  I definitely learned the definition for improvise.  There was no blackboard, 
so I used paper on a cork board to do a concept map.  It is hard to keep the students 
interested and on track.  We discussed the reasons that towns, such as Gouverneur, start 
on rivers.  The students were given the opportunity, with the concept map, to decide 
on the reasons without being told first.  They did a great job.  Some even thought 
they were being funny with some answers, but actually found out that they were right.<BR>
The students then made maps in groups of four.  We discussed working in groups, also. 
 The maps were of their own "made-up" cities on a river.  They did an excellent job 
and worked together fairly well.  Extra incentive for them was that the pictures 
we took of the maps might be on the internet.  Everybody proudly displayed the maps for 
the pictures.
