<TITLE>ritathre.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<STRONG>Friday, September 13th</STRONG>
<BR>
<BR>
Today we supposed to be a summing-up of the material covered during the week. I had 
two worksheets prepared to assess the students understanding of the material. What 
I learned early on that my plans were not going to work. The students were on hyperactive mode and had no intentions of settling down. I attempted to start a discussion about 
the week's lessons and the kids were more interested in the fact that it was Friday 
the 13th. Today was very challenging for me and I must say I had poor classroom management. I realize now that there were many factors working against me. For one the 
room I was sent to use with the kids was locked and so I had to spend time getting 
in. The room was overall a poor choice because it had far to many distractions all 
around it. I know now that these are preparation things that I will not let happen again but 
in my new setting I was unaware of these nuisances. I realize it sounds like I am 
making excuses for the poor class but these are just some of the factors I think 
attributed to the chaos. The most decidedly detrimental factor of the day was the behavior 
of a particularly dominant student. Her negative attitude just snowballed throughout 
the class. <BR>
I learned a lot today and am actually glad this situation happened. It made me aware 
of what I need to work on as far as management skills go and it also gave me ideas 
of potential problems which I will be able to recognize and hopefully avoid in the 
future. After class I was informed that the disruptive student had a serious dilemma in 
her life the night before and I instantly could understand her behavior.  Today's 
events made me even more confident in my career choice. I want to become better at 
my teaching skills so I can help these students to learn even when they are having a bad 
day. It was a great awakening that teaching is not always rainbows but that sometimes 
it pours. <BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="ritafour.html">Journal 4</A></H4>

</BODY>
</HTML>
