<BODY>
Donna J. Derrigo-Graves<BR>
<BR>
9-19-96<BR>
<BR>
To alleviate the cramped room, we went outside today to the outdoor classroom.  The 
students had a hard time staying focused with the great weather.  Writing in their 
journals did not come easily today.  They had been out in the field the previous 
day and wanted to talk about it.  I tried to get them to write what they were telling me 
in their journals.  They do not seem to like writing at all.  <BR>
We worked on projects where the students had to tell whether five pictures were of 
an ecosystem or a community (or both).  They did not work well in groups today, even 
trying to refuse to work with certain people.  Some people even lost their privilege 
to go to the union.  The ones that had to stay were given lessons on using the hand-held 
microscopes I had brought with me.  By doing this I tried to give these students 
more responsibility for the knowledge of the whole class.  They would have to show 
the other students how to use these instruments.
