<BODY>
<STRONG>Wednesday, Sept.18th<BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG></STRONG>
Today was our first field trip. It is amazing how the out of doors will bring out 
the excitement in teaching, especially biology. I had a wonderful time at Cranberry 
Lake as did all the students. It was no challenge getting the kids involved. In fact, 
it was tougher to keep them out of the water. Ideally, I would love to always teach outside 
but I realize that is impractical. I am a firm supporter of hands on learning after 
seeing firsthand the excitement it generates.<BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="ritafive.html">Journal 5</A></H4>

</BODY>
