<BODY>
Melissa Plemons<BR>
Journal #4 <BR>
Monday Sept. 30,1996<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Again, I want to comment upon the trip to Fine last Wednesday.  I think the kids actually 
look forward to going out in the field, maybe even the highlight of their weeks. 
 They behave extremely well and work really well too.  I enjoy it just as much as 
they do I'm sure.  One student actually is very adept at capturing and finding creatures. 
 Once you get him going, he finds them left and right.  I am concerned about one 
student; she is afraid to touch anything and doesn't look or try to look for anything. 
 That isn't what the purpose of our field trips is.   <BR>
<BR>
Our five week mark is due into Mr. Vandenburg by Thursday.  One student doesn't even 
come on Mondays and I am afraid he will fail. The worst part is, he does a great 
job in the field.   I guess it is really hard for me to grade them- some are great 
learners, but they don't like to pay attention to directions, or they fool around when I 
am talking, or if they have to do work.  I got so fed up with them today that I just 
told them to leave. That I wasn't going to teach them if all they wanted to do was 
fool around.  Mr. Vandenberg came in and gave them a talk and made them feel like lousy. 
 Then they apologized and a few stayed after to learn how to read the key.  I really 
am most mad that now we can't look for animals at the site on Wednesday because they 
have to get leaves the correct way in order to identify them on Thursday with Mrs. Graves. 
 They weren't allowed to go to the gym today and they aren't allowed to go to the 
union on Thursday.  I feel bad for them, but Mike said to establish the discipline 
early.  I'm trying! <BR>
