<TITLE>Sept.26 Donna [v4.0]</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Donna J. Derrigo-Graves<BR>
<BR>
9/26/96<BR>
<BR>
Since we still had not found a room, we went to the computer lab today.  This excited 
the kids.  They were exceptionally good when going through the library.  They again 
worked in groups of two.  Names of organisms were found in field guides, which they 
used quite well.  The organisms were ones that were found at the field the previous 
day.  The computers were used to show how hierarchial classification is set up.  
The "tree of life," from a web page, was used to see the branches made in this system. 
 The students went from kingdom to species with Homo sapiens to see the way the classification 
is used.<BR>
The student's group work was exceptional today.  They were really interested with 
the Net and easily navigated from page to page.  They listened very well today.
<!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="donnafive.html">Go to journal 5</A>
</BODY>
