<BODY>
<STRONG>Friday, September 20th</STRONG>
<BR>
<BR>
Today went very well. We identified the specimens we gathered at Cranberry Lake and 
prepared a presentation of our findings to the Chemistry Group. The students were 
really interested in talking about the plants and animals they found but were nervous 
about presenting in front of their peers. I plan to continue having the students present 
throughout the semester to increase their exposure and hopefully increase their confidence. 
We also played a vocabulary game where the students were being assessed on their knowledge of the vocabulary. Each student was out for them self so they were not 
allowed to talk with their peers during the game. Half of the class were given definitions 
and the other half were given the appropriate term and the students had to pair up without talking. It was fun to watch because some of the students had real difficulties 
at first in not talking. <BR>
after class I tutored students individually. I really liked being able to do this. 
It is great to be able to work on a one-to-one basis. I think it helped the students 
the students better but I believe I gained the most from it because it allowed me 
to get to know the students better.<BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="ritasix.html">Journal 6</A></H4>

</BODY>
</HTML>
