<BODY>
Melissa Plemons<BR>
Journal #5<BR>
Friday October 11,1996<BR>
<BR>
 I taught for Rita today because she taught for me on Friday.  I was a little intimidated 
at first because I am not familiar with the procedure she usually follows.  Fridays 
are for review and a tying together of all the material that was covered that week.  She also does anything that didn't get finished for that week. Rita had also 
said that the kids were high strung on Fridays because of the coming weekend.  I 
was also nervous about that.  <BR>
Well, it went well because they were being punished for not having there homework 
done.  I gave them a "pop" quiz first thing.  They moaned and groaned about that, 
saying that it was hard.  I thought maybe the quiz would stress to them the importance 
of this class, and the determination of their grade for Mike.  I believe they took this 
one seriously, because they were pretty quiet afterwards.  The remainder of the class 
was devoted to finishing any behind homework.  They weren't allowed to go to their 
usual gym today because they still didn't finish everything.  I think only two people 
had their work all caught up.  The others were complaining about how everyone in 
school was always on their case.  I told them that they only had to do their homework 
and no one would bother them.  One student said, "I'm going to get all of my homework done 
this weekend, so people will get off my back".  I hope he does.  <BR>
They were rowdy though.  Not a much as the Chemistry students, but they were anxious 
to go home.  I stayed until they left at 3:00 and they were bouncing off the walls 
waiting for the final bell to ring.  Mike gave several lectures about their behavior 
and several minutes were added to their school day at the end because they couldn't 
 calm down.  I thought that I was the only one who has problems with them, but I 
realized that they are like that for everybody, not only me!<BR>
