<TITLE>Oct.3 Donna [v4.0]</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Donna J. Derrigo-Graves<BR>
<BR>
10/3/96<BR>
<BR>
We started off the day with a discussion about group work.  The students had gotten 
in trouble on Monday and we discussed why.  The incident seemed to bring them very 
down.  They lacked the motivation they had had previous days.  Although we had a 
good time, I had to mark them off a lot for being a little too loud, not paying attention 
and not being polite.  We classified leaves together and they easily performed the 
task.  They became bored.<BR>
I gave them an assignment to work on a Botany cartoon.  I told them to have fun with 
it, that seemed to alleviate the problem they had with it.  This was the first time 
I have given them an assignment.  All in all, it was a good day for us to get to 
know each other, but it was not a productive day.  
</BODY>
</HTML>
