<H2>THE INCREDIBLE JOURNEY </H2>
by Bobby Newcombe<BR>
<BR>
Once there was a water drop called Fred.  His birthday was today, October 18,  and 
he is 5,000,000,001.   The one and most important journey was when Fred, the water 
drop, went to the Middle East where they do not like to drink Coca Cola.  The one 
and only thing they like to drink is water and Pepsi.  Fred was shoved into a Pepsi can and 
then down Mrs. French's throat.  Eventually he wound up outside again and began to 
evaporate.  He went to the clouds and when it rained, he went into a pasture.  He 
was licked up by a thirsty cow.  One day the cow went near the river and went to the bathroom. 
 Fred came out and went down the river.  He was eventually sucked into this great 
big tunnel and into the Water Filtration plant.  Today, on his birthday, he is going 
through this cycle again as he is constantly being recycled.<BR>
<H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="bioseven.html">Journal 7</A></H4>
