<BODY>
<STRONG>Wednesday, September 25th<BR>
</STRONG>
<STRONG><BR>
</STRONG>
Today was another wonderful field experience. The site we found was perfect, complete 
with a beaver dam. The students really seem excited and interested on the trips. 
We finished early and I let my group explore. We followed the river until we came 
upon a stream draining into the river. We followed the stream up as far as we were able 
to and came upon a large culvert  under a major highway which drained farm land run-off 
into the Oswegatchie. The lessons here seemed endless and the students loved the 
fact that they found the site on their own. I had the group inform the other groups what 
they found and explain the effects of the run-off on the river. I was especially 
proud of one student who actually tackled her fear of touching frogs by catching 
one to show the group!<BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="ritaseve.html">Journal 7</A></H4>

</BODY>
