<H2>THE INCREDIBLE JOURNEY </H2>
by Kelly Mitchell<BR>
<BR>
Mike, the water drop, turned five billion one one years old today.  I am here to tell 
you about his life.  Well, when Mike, the water drop, first came into this world, 
he was coming out of the sky as rain and landed in a lake where Corry, the dinosaur, 
 drank.  Corry accidentally drank Mike and down Mike went.  A couple hours later, he 
cam out on the ground and it sopped him up like it was dying of thirst.  All of a 
sudden, he was sucked up by plant and into it's pollen.  Then came along Buz, the 
bee, and scooped up Mike with the pollen.  As he rode on the pollen, he slipped right off and 
landed right in the lake by the filtration plant.  He was sucked into this huge pipe 
and when he came out, he was so clean and purified that he felt weird because of 
all the stuff he had been through.  He then went into Billy Bobs well and was there for 
years and years.  Finally, Billy Bob died and a new family moved in and drank Mike 
up.  Now today he is inside little Suzzy waiting to go through some more way cool 
adventures.  He also hopes little Suzzy let's him go before this day is up because today is 
his five billion and first birthday.<BR>
<H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="bioeight.html">Journal 8</A></H4>
