<BODY>
<STRONG>Friday, September 27th</STRONG>
<BR>
<BR>
Today was designated game day. The biology and chemistry teams were divided as evenly 
as we could determine and regrouped as two teams with both biology and chemistry 
members. Mrs. Heise and I borrowed a tic-tac-toe game board made by Mrs. McGuire. 
Mrs. Heise and I alternated asking chem and bio questions. I was presently surprised by 
what some of the students knew. It was a nice reward to see students I was concerned 
about answering questions confidently. The students worked well together and it was 
a blast! After the game, the winning team was allowed to chose one of the two bags of candy 
brought in by Mrs. Heise and myself. The other team received the remaining bag of 
candy. I liked the excitement that the competition brought to the class. After class, 
I tutored individual students and was impressed with the amount of pride the students 
showed when they informed me of how many answers they knew. Mrs. Heise and I plan 
on continuing game days occasionally since this one was so successful.<BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="ritaeigh.html">Journal 8</A></H4>

</BODY>
