<BODY>

<H2>HERBY THE WATER DROP </H2>
by Jason Woodard<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
The journey began when Herby was a year old.  His mom told him to stay around the 
area but he didn't.  His mom was talking to another water drop and he took off.  
He traveled down the bank of the river and began to whistle.  He came up to a pipe 
and went in.  He came out and saw a stream.  He went down the stream.  When he got up to a 
fork, like a Y, he went left.  <BR>
While his mother was talking, she turned around and saw the Herby wasn't there.  She 
started calling Herby but he didn't answer.  Meanwhile, Herby was just passing through 
a river.  He came upon another pipe and went in.<BR>
In five million years, his mother is still worried about him and he still hasn't come 
home.  Herby was in a pipe and headed for this thin pipe and he ended up in a filtering 
thing.  Finally he was in someone's glass.  When she was drinking, he dropped out of the glass and landed on the floor.  While he was on the floor, this lady mopped 
him up and he was in the mop bucket.   <BR>
 His mom was still looking for him.  A thousand years had passed and she still couldn't 
find him.  <BR>
When he was in the bucket, the lady dumped all the water out on the ground and he 
was taken underground and eventually floated down the stream and ended up in a river. 
 <BR>
His mother stopped looking for him and she got home.  "He'll come home.  He's now 
on his way home", she said.  <BR>
Herby started down the river and ended up floating down by a cow that was drinking. 
 The cow drank Herby.  Herby said, " Is this a cave or am I in a cow's stomach?" 
 The cow went to the bathroom and Herby started back home.  He knew his mother was 
waiting for him.  He made it home and told his mother that he was walking and started downstream 
and that he was in a cow's stomach and that he ended up back home.<BR>
And that is how Herby got to be Herby the Adventurer.<BR>
<H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="students.html">Journal 9</A></H4>
</BODY>
</HTML>
