<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Chapter 2A</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><B>II.   FACULTY APPOINTMENT AND EMPLOYMENT</B></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<dt><br>
<dl>
<dt><b>A.	I<A NAME="a">MMIGRATION REFORM AND CONTROL ACT OF 1986-COMPLIANCE POLICY AND PROCEDURE</A></b>
<dt><br>
	In November 1986, the Immigration Reform and Control Act became Law.  This Act requires that all prospective employees provide proof of, and certify to, their identity and employment eligibility.  In compliance with this Act, SUNY Potsdam has adopted the following policy and procedures.
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt>1.	<i><A NAME="a1">POLICY</A></i>
<dt><br>
		It is the policy of SUNY Potsdam to employ only United States citizens or aliens lawfully admitted to the United States and permitted by the United States Department of Labor to seek and accept employment.  Effective November 6, 1986, and continuing thereafter, no person offered employment by SUNY Potsdam shall be permitted to commence his/her duties or obligations without first having satisfactorily completed the required Employment Eligibility Certification (I-9) procedure.
<dt><br>
		This policy applies to all persons (including undergraduate and graduate students) who are offered employment with or who are to receive assistantships from SUNY Potsdam or the Research Foundation.  All offers of employment are contingent upon completion of the I-9 certification.
</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt>2.	<i><A NAME="a2">PROCEDURES</A></i>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
		<dt>a)	A copy of the policy and an I-9 certification form will be included with the offer of employment.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt>b)	Part I of the I-9 form (Employee Information and Verification) is to be completed, signed and presented with one or more of the required document(s) to the appropriate office as follows:

			<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt>i)	The Office of Human Resources will examine and certify identification and employment eligibility for all students, classified and unclassified employees appointed to the State payroll.

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt>ii)	The Office of Continuing Education will examine and certify identification and employment eligibility for off-campus, continuing education, and summer session faculty, students and staff appointed to the State payroll.

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt>iii)	The Financial Aid Office will examine and certify identification and employment eligibility for all students appointed to the Federal Work Study payrolls.

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt>iv)	The Office of Human Resources will examine and certify identification and employment eligibility for all individuals appointed to the Research Foundation Payroll.
<dt><br>
	A list of the legal documents that may be submitted to establish identity and/or employment eligibility is available from the Office of Human Resources.
</dl><BR><BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="S2B.html>Continue to next section</A>
<BR>
<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>

