<html>
<head>
<title> Chapter 6D</title>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS"><CENTER><B>VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS</B></CENTER></A>
<br><br>
<dt>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6D"><b>D</A>.	LOANS</b>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6D1"><i>1</A>.	TIER 1 AND TIER 2</i>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6D1a">a</A>)	Eligibility
<dt><br>
			<dt>Loans can be granted only to members who have credit for at least one year of member service, and have annuity savings.  Only one loan is permitted in any three month period.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6D1b">b</A>)	Terms
<dt><br?
			<dt>The application will be processed for the amount requested, unless that amount exceeds the maximum permitted under the law, generally 75% of the member's total annuity savings less any outstanding loan balance.  In that case a check will be issued for the maximum amount permitted.  Minimum loan is $25.00.  The minimum repayments must be an amount sufficient to repay the loan by age seventy, and not less than $3.00 if paid weekly, $5.00 if bi-weekly or semi-monthly, or $10.00 if monthly.  Loan repayments will be in even dollar amounts.  If you have contributions on deposit and a loan outstanding on the effective date of your retirement, part or all of the unpaid loan balance may constitute interest which was credited to your annuity savings account and therefore be subject to Federal income tax in the year you retire.  Since this income tax would not be payable until you retire, information regarding the taxable amount will be furnished to you at that time.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dt><A NAME="6D2"><i>2</A>.	TIER 3 AND 4</i>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6D2a">a</A>)	Loan Application Requirements
<dt><br>
			<dt>You must have a minimum of one full year of service credit and be on the payroll of the State or a participating employer.  If you are on an unpaid leave of absence you are not eligible to borrow.
<Dt><br>
<Dt>You may borrow only once in a twelve month period.
<dt><br>
<dt>Loans may be made for up to seventy-five percent of your retirement contributions, but must be for at least $1,000.  If your current contribution balance, including interest, does not total at least $1,334 you are not yet loan eligible.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6D2b">b</A>)	Loan Repayments
<dt><br>
			<dt>Loan repayments will be withheld from your paycheck.  Loans must be repaid in equal installments in an amount sufficient to repay the loan, insurance premiums, and interest on the unpaid balance within a five year period.  Payments may not be less than two percent of your salary.  Loan repayment deductions will be in even dollar amounts.  Loans may be prepaid at any time with no prepayment penalties.
<dt><br>
<dt>Your outstanding loan balance will be shown on your annual member statement as of March 31st of each year.  You may also request, in writing, a statement of your outstanding loan balance at any time.

		</dl>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6D2c">c</A>)	Interest Rates
<dt><br>
			<dt>Interest rates will be determined each fiscal year for loans taken in that year.  The rate will be one percent less than the rate used by the Retirement System in its annual actuarial valuation.  The rate in effect at that time a loan is made will remain constant for the length of the loan.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6E2d">d</A>)	Touch Tone Loan Information
<dt><br>
<dt>If you have questions about a loan, call 518-473-1355.  You will need your social security number and date of birth.
</dl>
</dl>
</dl>
<br><br>
