<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Chapter 4G</TITLE></HEAD>
<!-- Body Tag --><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF1FFF"> 

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><strong>IV.  FACULTY COMPENSATION</strong></CENTER> 
	<dt><br><BR>

<dd><dl>
<dt>G.	<strong><!-- Anchor Point Tag --><A NAME="Deferred Compensation Plan">DEFERRED COMPENSATION PLAN</A></strong> 
<dt><br>
	The State Deferred Compensation Plan permits an eligible employee to invest through payroll deduction in Plan options.  The amount invested under the plan is not subject to Federal or State income taxes and is subtracted from gross salary prior to the calculation of withholding taxes.  The income earned is tax exempt.  Taxes are  paid upon distribution of the funds.  Contributions may be invested in a money market fund, a guaranteed or fixed income fund or an equity (stock) fund and may increase or decrease as the employee's financial situation changes.  Information is available from the Office of Human Resources or directly from The Copeland Companies.

</dl>

<br><br>
