		<dt><br>
<dd><dl><!-- 2 -->
	<dt><A NAME="09A4a">a</A>)	Allied Health Professions
<dt><br>
			<dt>Students interested in pursuing a specific health-related career other than dentistry, medicine or veterinary medicine may begin their undergraduate studies at SUNY Potsdam in preparation for transferring to an institution offering the professional career of choice.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4b">b</A>)	Art Education Program With St. Lawrence University
<dt><br>
			<dt>Art Studio majors may obtain art teacher certification by completing this program offered through the Associated Colleges.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4c">c</A>)	1-1-2 Programs with Canton College of Technology
<dt><br>
			<dt>Undergraduates can utilize course sequence at Canton           enabling them to receive not only the bachelor of arts      degree from Potsdam, but an associate degree from Canton as well.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4d">d</A>)	3-2 Programs With SUNY College of Technology at Utica/Rome
<dt><br>
<dt>SUNY Potsdam and SUNY College of Technology at Utica/Rome have a formal 3 - 2 program affiliation in the areas of accounting, management and engineering technology.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4e">e</A>)	Career Experience Program (CEP)
<dt><br>
			<dt>The program is based upon the belief that career-related work experience during college contributes to learning in the classroom and to greater productivity after college, and student initiative is necessary to launch a career successfully.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4f">f</A>)	Center For Independent Scholars

			<dt><br>
<dd><dl><!-- 3 -->
	<dt><A NAME="09A4fi">i</A>)	Purpose
<dt><br>
				<dt>Founded by Action of the Associated Colleges Board of Trustees in Fall, 1984, the Center for Independent      Scholars  offers its Fellows the opportunity to pursue scholarly and professional interests in ways generally unavailable to those not employed by academic institutions.
<dt><br>
				<dt>By definition, Fellows are scholars holding at least a master's degree, who are unaffiliated with any institution, but who wish to pursue serious scholarly work.  Such work could include writing, or preparation for a conference presentation.

			<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4fii">ii</A>)	Benefits to Scholars
<dt><br>
				<dt>Center Appointment Provides Fellows With:
<dt><br>
				<dt>. A place to work<br>
				<dt>. Courtesy appointment in an appropriate department<br>
				<dt>. Library privileges at any member institution<br>
				<dt>. Proximity to others with similar goals
              
			<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4fiii">iii</A>)	Obligation Of Scholars
<dt><br>
				<dt>Center Fellows Are Expected To:
<dt><br>
				<dt>. Make a yearly public presentation based on their work<br>
				<dt>. Participate in the life of the Center<br>
				<dt>. Serve as a role model to unaffiliated academics and to students<br>
				<dt>. Acknowledge support of the Center and the appointing institution in publications, conference attendance and   presentations

			<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4fiv">iv</A>)	Appointment To The Center
<dt><br>
				<dt>Each center appointment is made by a member institution of the Associated Colleges and each has its own internal process.  Generally, the offices of the academic deans, or Provost will coordinate institutional efforts.  Departmental involvement in the appointment process in likely given the courtesy appointment accompanying membership.  Confirming action on appointments is taken by the Associated College's Board.
</dl><!-- 3 -->
		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4g">g</A>)	Cross-Registration
<dt><br>
			<dt>Cross-registration provides an opportunity for full-time  matriculated students at SUNY Canton, Clarkson University, SUNY Potsdam and St. Lawrence University to take up to two (2) courses per academic year (including summer session(s)) at any of the other institutions on a space available basis.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4h">h</A>)	Engineering Double Degree Program
<dt><br>
			<dt>Students who wish to combine their interests in the liberal arts and sciences with competence  in a field of engineering may enroll in a five-year program leading to a B.A. degree, awarded by the State University College of Arts and Science at Potsdam and a B.S. degree awarded by Clarkson University.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4i">i</A>)	Four Semester Completion Plan
<dt><br>
			<dt>The State University of New York was created to assure comprehensive educational opportunities in higher education for all citizens of the State.  To facilitate movement between institutions, the Board of Trustees resolved in 1972 and reaffirmed in 1980 the policy:  "A New York State resident who is a graduate of a State University of New York two year College...and who possesses an Associate in Arts or an Associate in Science degree shall be guaranteed an opportunity to continue his/her education on a full-time basis at a senior campus of the University...".
<dt><br>
<dt>Under this articulation policy, students accepted at SUNY Potsdam may, in selected programs identified in the Articulation Guide, complete the B.A. within four additional semesters of study, assuming satisfactory progress.  All students selecting the four-semester completion plan will work out a program of study with an academic advisor at the time of admission and will be expected to adhere to this program.  Changes in the four- semester completion plan will require consent of the advisor.
<dt><br>
<dt>Students selecting programs not listed in the Articulation Guide or wishing to complete supplementary credentials may find that special requirements or internship preclude completion of all degree requirements in only four semesters.  In these instances, SUNY Potsdam commits itself to working out a program of study with the student that leads to graduation within the shortest time possible beyond the limit of four semesters.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4j">j</A>)	International Education Program
<dt><br>
			<dt>A program for students wishing to study abroad.
               
		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4k">k</A>)	Internships
<dt><br>
			<dt>Internships are forms of academically supervised learning that normally take place outside the classroom and are not covered by the existing definition of "tutorial."          

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4l">l</A>)	MBA 4 + 1 Program
<dt><br>
			<dt>SUNY Potsdam and the School of Management at Clarkson have cooperated in establishing a program which guides students in planning their undergraduate programs to include courses which serve as a foundation for graduate work in management.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4m">m</A>)	Faculty Exchange Center
<dt><br>
			<dt>SUNY Potsdam is a member of the Faculty Exchange Center (FEC) which publishes a list of faculty in the U.S. and abroad who are interested in exchange opportunities.  The FEC does now broker the exchanges.  It also publishes a house-exchange supplement.
<dt><br>
<dt>Further information is available from the Office of the Associate Provost.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4n">n</A>)	National Student Exchange Program (NSE)
<dt><br>
<dt>The National Student Exchange is a membership organization which links universities and colleges in the United States in order to provide students an exchange opportunity to an institution of higher learning in another area of this country.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4o">o</A>)	Potsdam Student Ambassador Program
<dt><br>
<dt>Potsdam Student Ambassadors are upper-class student volunteers who visit employers in their home area providing information about SUNY Potsdam services and programs.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4p">p</A>)	Pre-Legal Studies
<dt><br>
<dt>For students interested in pursuing careers in law.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4q">q</A>)	Pre-Medical Studies
<dt><br>
<dt>For students interested in pursuing careers in dentistry,                medicine, and veterinary medicine.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4r">r</A>)	President's Scholars Program
   <dt><br>
			<dt>In order to strengthen Potsdam's reputation as one of the most selective of the Colleges of Arts and Sciences in SUNY and to complement our admissions and recruiting efforts, the President's Scholars Program has been established. This program is conceived as a means of focusing our recruiting efforts on a special constituency of the College that we may not have attracted in the past in as great a number as would seem desirable.
<dt><br>
<dt>In the instance of the President's Scholars Program, it is  intended that we focus on the recruitment of outstanding students with scholarly interests who could particularly benefit from and contribute to the special environment of SUNY Potsdam.
<dt><br>
<dt>A small group of President's Scholars will be established.  Criteria for initial selection will include high achievement in school grades and SAT/ACT scores and strong letters of recommendation.
<dt><br>
<dt>We are seeking students with demonstrated academic interests and students with a well-developed intellectual curiosity who would help to foster and benefit from an increased intellectual atmosphere in the campus community.
<dt><br>
<dt>During their Potsdam tenure, the President's Scholars will be assigned to work with an advising team composed of the Dean of their respective schools and at least one faculty member in their proposed disciplinary field.  The advising team will serve as mentors and will work with each student to develop a special course of study.  This course of study might include, in addition to standard offerings, certain tutorial opportunities and internships which could be arranged with the assistance of the mentors and the departments.  Course registration priority will be provided these students.
<dt><br>
<dt>The individualized programs will contain the customary curricular ingredients expected of all students:  a general education requirement, a major concentration and so on.  But these requirements may be fulfilled in original or specially tailored way.
<dt><br>
<dt>Overall, the President's Scholars Program will be distinguished by the personal attention afforded excellent students within our academic community.  In addition, it is deemed imperative that we provide every opportunity for communication, at all levels, among President's Scholars.
<Dt><br>
<dt>A special council for the President's Scholars Program consisting of some of our most distinguished and respected teacher-scholars have been charged with the maintenance of standards and assisting in the recruitment and selection of scholars and their advisement after arrival on campus.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4s">s</A>)	Program With SUNY College of Optometry
<dt><br>
			<dt>SUNY Potsdam and SUNY College of Optometry have a formal affiliation in optometric education. This is a seven year preoptometry/optometry program of study.


		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4t">t</A>)	Reserve Officers Training Corps (ROTC) Programs With Clarkson University
<dt><br>
<dt>In cooperation with Clarkson University Reserve Officers Training Corps programs for both the U.S. Air Force and the U.S. Army are offered to SUNY Potsdam students.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4u">u</A>)	Student Initiated Interdepartmental Major (SIIM)
     <dt><br>
			<dt>The SIIM is administered by the Interdepartmental                Programs Committee.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4v">v</A>)	Student Teaching in England
<dt><br>
			<dt>Selected elementary and secondary students may do half (8 weeks) of their student teaching in the public schools of Lincoln, England, in cooperation with Bishop Grosseteste College.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4w">w</A>)	Tutorial Or Independent Study
<dt><br>
			<dt>For certain purposes - to allow students to investigate areas for which there is not sufficient demand to warrant a regular course offering, to allow students to pursue research interests that cannot be met by an existing advanced course, or to allow interdisciplinary investigation under two or more instructors where existing courses do not provide such opportunities - students may undertake tutorial or "independent" study.

		<dt><br>
	<dt><A NAME="09A4x">x</A>)	Visiting Student Program (VSP)   
<dt><br>
			<dt>As a student attending a college or university in New York State, you are eligible to study at another institution of your choice in the State.
</dl><!-- 2 -->
</dl><!-- 1 -->
<dt><br>
</dl><!-- 0 -->
<BR>
