<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Chapter 9 E</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR><center><strong>IX. ACADEMIC AFFAIRS</strong></center><br>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09E"><b>E</a>.	UNIVERSITY GRANTS, AWARDS, AND PROGRAMS</b>
<dt><br>
	<dt>The vitality of its teaching and research are essential to the quality of the State University of New York.
<dt><br>
<dt>The University, through a variety of programs, seeks to facilitate the professional growth and renewal of its faculty.  At the same time, it has made provision to recognize formally, outstanding accomplishments and talents of its faculty and other campus personnel.  The University provides several grant and award programs to accomplish these purposes.
<dt><br>
<dt>Guidelines, forms, information and assistance for the following programs are available from the Office of Faculty Scholarships and Grants. 

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09E1"><i>1</a>.	DISTINGUISHED PROFESSORS, DISTINGUISHED TEACHING PROFESSORS AND DISTINGUISHED SERVICE PROFESSORS</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>A description of each program is given in Section II.  Faculty Appointment and Employment.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09E2"><i>2</a>.	CHANCELLOR'S AWARD FOR EXCELLENCE IN TEACHING</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Nominees may be of any academic rank and must have completed at least three academic years of full-time teaching on the recommending campus prior to the year of nomination.  Department chairpersons may be nominated for the award contingent upon the individual's carrying the campus-defined full-time teaching load for persons performing such administrative responsibilities.  The primary criterion for the Chancellor's Award for Excellence in Teaching is skill in teaching, although consideration is given to sound scholarship (usually demonstrated through publications or artistic productions) and service to the University and to the campus.  In the selection of persons to be nominated for these awards the following criteria are to be used:
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	TEACHING TECHNIQUES AND REPRESENTATIVE MATERIALS
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	SCHOLARSHIP AND PROFESSIONAL GROWTH; STUDENT SERVICES
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	ACADEMIC STANDARDS AND EVALUATION OF REQUIREMENTS AND STUDENTS PERFORMANCE
<Dt><br>
		<dt>Campus deadline for receipt of nominations:  March

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09E3"><i>3</a>.	CHANCELLOR'S AWARD FOR EXCELLENCE IN LIBRARIANSHIP</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Nominations for the award must be drawn from persons having a full-time appointment as a professional librarian for at least three years at the nominating campus.  Possession of an MLS is required.  Only the individual who serves as head of campus library (or the person who heads all campus libraries for institutions with multiple libraries) is ineligible for nomination for this award.  (These individuals are eligible for nomination for the Excellence in Professional Service Award.)  Nominees for the award need not have along record of service, but performance must have been extraordinary in the following areas:
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	SKILL IN LIBRARIANSHIP; SERVICE TO THE UNIVERSITY AND TO THE PROFESSION
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	SCHOLARSHIP AND CONTINUING PROFESSIONAL GROWTH
<Dt><br>
	<dt>Campus deadline for receipt of nominations:  March

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09E4"><i>4</a>.	CHANCELLOR'S AWARD FOR EXCELLENCE IN PROFESSIONAL SERVICE</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Nominations for the award must be drawn from individuals presently serving in full-time professional service (not classified) capacities with more than 50 percent of the assignment in non teaching services.  Specific categories included for this award are academic instructional and research support technologies, and the individual who is the director of the campus libraries.  Persons nominated must have completed at least three years of continuous full-time professional service in the position for which nominated.  The following are the selection criteria for nomination for the award:
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	WITHIN THE POSITION DESCRIPTION-The candidate must perform superbly in fulfilling the job description for the position held.
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	BEYOND THE POSITION DESCRIPTION-The candidate should also demonstrate excellence in professional activities beyond the parameters of the job description.  The ideal candidate will satisfy the standards in a creative and innovative fashion while demonstrating flexibility and adaptability to institutional needs.  Consideration should be given to capabilities and accomplishments in the areas of leadership, decision making, and problem solving.  Evidence in this category would include professional recognition, initiation of ideas, committee activities, etc.
<dt><br>
<dt>Campus deadline for receipt of nominations:  March

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09E5"><i>5</a>.	CONVERSATIONS IN THE DISCIPLINES</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Conversations fund inter-campus conferences which bring together State University faculty and visiting scholars to examine new trends, review promising findings, and better acquaint faculty with professional developments in their fields and on other campuses.  By such interchange, both the personal and professional growth of individuals and the programs of instruction and research at participating campuses are enhanced.
<dt><br>
<dt>The emphasis of the program is upon scholarly and creative development, rather than administrative, curricular, or instructional matters.  By such interchange, both the personal and professional growth of individuals and the programs of instruction and research at participating campuses are enhanced.
<dt><br>
<Dt>The campus hosting the conference administers these inter-campus gatherings.  No rigid formula is applied in determining the number of colleges that should participate in the "Conversation."
<Dt><br>
<Dt>A sum not to exceed $2,500 will be made available to support each approved conference.  Since 1965, more than 340 "Conversations" have been held on various campuses in numerous disciplines.
      <Dt><br>     
<dt>Deadline for receipt of applications:  March.

</dl>
</dl>
<BR>
<B><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="S9F.html">Continue to next section</A></B>
