<HEAD>
<TITLE>Chapter 9  F</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<center><strong>IX. ACADEMIC AFFAIRS</strong></center><br>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F"><b>F</a>.	PRESIDENT'S AWARDS AND CAMPUS GRANT PROGRAMS</b>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F1"><i>1</a>.	EXCELLENCE IN TEACHING</i><BR>
<BR>
<dt>
		<dt>The award is open to teaching faculty who have completed, by January 15, at least one academic year of full-time employment at SUNY Potsdam and who teach as a part of their normal duties a minimum of six semester hours of classes.  Excellence in Teaching awards are based on the following criteria:
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Demonstrated excellence in techniques of instruction, availability and help to students
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Growth in one's field of instruction, concern for intellectual growth of students
<Dt><br>
		<dd>-	Adherence to high standards, positive attitude towards the profession.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F2"><i>2</a>.	EXCELLENCE IN PUBLIC SERVICE</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>The award is open to all faculty and professional staff of SUNY Potsdam who have completed at least one academic year of full-time employment by January 15.  Excellence in Public Service is based on the following criteria:
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Performance of job-related duties in an outstanding manner
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Meaningful participation in public service activities which are an extension of professional training.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F3"><i>3</A>.	EXCELLENCE IN RESEARCH AND CREATIVE ENDEAVOR</i>
<dt><br>
		The award is open to all faculty who have completed, by January 15, at least one year of full-time employment at SUNY Potsdam.  Excellence in Research and Creative Endeavors is based on the following criteria:
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Investigation or creation which has enlarged the store of human knowledge, or has expanded the potential of human creativity.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F4"><i>4</a>.	EXCELLENCE IN PROFESSIONAL SERVICE</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>The award is open to all professional and managerial/confidential employees of SUNY Potsdam who have completed, by January 15, at least one academic year of full-time employment and who are not eligible for the President's Award for Excellence in Academic Service.  Excellence in Professional Service is based on the following criteria:
<dt><br>
		<Dd>-	Outstanding performance of one's duties
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Demonstrated decisiveness, creativity, innovation and contemporary understanding of one's field
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Significant and successful contributions to the College.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F5"><i>5</a>.	EXCELLENCE IN ACADEMIC SERVICE</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>The award is open to all categories of professional staff of the Information Services area (College's Libraries, Computing Services and Tele-Media Engineering) who have completed, by January 15, at least one year of full-time employment at SUNY Potsdam.  Because this award is exclusively for the above-mentioned categories of faculty and staff, they are ineligible for the president's Awards for Excellence in Professional Service.  Excellence in Academic Service is based on the following criteria:
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Superb performance of one's duties with appropriate flexibility and adaptability to the College's needs
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Exceeding the usual standards of performance in a creative and innovative way; exhibiting a positive attitude toward one's professional unit and toward the College generally.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F6"><i>6</a>.	EXCELLENCE IN ACADEMIC ADVISING</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>The award is open to all faculty of Potsdam College of SUNY who will have completed at least one year of full-time teaching and advising by January 15.  Excellence in Academic Advising is based on the following criteria:
<dt><br>
		<dd>-	Availability to students beyond regular office hours, initiative in reaching out to advisees
<Dt><br>
		<dd>-	Knowledge of resources and services to give a student additional help
<Dt><br>
		<dd>-	Concern for students shown by assisting them in contacting other needed resources 
<Dt><br>
		<dd>-	Long-range interest in students by discussing total program
<dt><br>
		<dt>Ability to show advisees all available academic and career options, while not trying to decide for them.
<dt><br>
<dt>All President's Awards may be won only once in a five year period.
<dt><br>
<dt>Deadline for receipt of nominations:  February

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F7"><i>7</a>.	MINI-GRANTS</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Mini-Grant funding for joint student-faculty projects relating to research, creative endeavors, public service, instruction, or learning are available.  The maximum award per project is $500.  At least eight proposals are to be funded.  The term Faculty includes all employees occupying positions designated by the Chancellor of the State University of New York as being in the unclassified service, i.e., includes all members of the Professional Staff; students may be full-time or part-time, graduate or undergraduate.
<dt><br>
<dt>Deadline for receipt of applications:  September.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F8"><i>8</a>.	RESEARCH AND CREATIVE ENDEAVORS PROGRAM</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>The Research and Creative Endeavors Program is designed to encourage faculty to plan their professional growth and to seek and attract external funding for their work.  As in the past, in making awards, the Committee will especially emphasize projects that have the potential to encourage new faculty, women and minorities; to support research and creative endeavors across the disciplines, and to attract external resources.  It is anticipated that most requests will be within the $500-$2,000 range.
<dt><br>
<dt>Deadline for receipt of applications:  October, February & April.	

</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
	<dt><A NAME="09F9"><i>9</a>.	FACULTY UNDERGRADUATE SUMMER RESEARCH PROGRAM (F-USRP)</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>This program will support up to seven faculty-student projects during the summer.  Students will receive a stipend of $2,400 for ten weeks of full-time assistance on a faculty member's research program.  In addition, a double occupancy room will be provide free of charge.  The faculty member will receive a grant of up to $500 for expenses related to the proposed project.
<dt><br>
<dt>Deadline for receipt of applications:  February.
</dl>
</dl>

<BR>


