<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Chapter 6A</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<center>
<A NAME="VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS"><B>VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS</B></A>
</center>
<br><br><br>
A.  <A NAME="06A"><B>RETIREMENT PROGRAMS</B></A>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><BLOCKQUOTE>1.  <A NAME="06A1"><i>PROGRAMS AVAILABLE</i></A>
<dt><br>
<dt>Members of the professional service staff of the College are eligible to elect one of the following three retirement programs.
<dt><br>
<dd><dl><!-- 1 -->
<dt>a)  New York State Teachers' Retirement System (TRS)
<dt><br>
<dt>b)  New York State Employees' Retirement System (ERS)
<dt><br>
<dt>c)  The Optional Retirement Program established by law, under which State University has designated the Teachers Insurance and Annuity Association and the College Retirement Equities Fund (TIAA-CREF) as the insurers.
</dl><!-- 1 -->
<dt><br>
<dt>2.  <A NAME="06A2"><i>CHOOSING A RETIREMENT PROGRAM</I></A>
<dt><br>
<dt>All full-time employees must elect to participate in one of these programs within 30 days of the effective date of his/her employment.  If he/she does not make a timely election, the employee will then be required to join TRS.
<dt><br>
<dt>This is the only opportunity an employee will have to make an election once he/she becomes a participant in one of these programs, either through election or by failure to make a timely election, he/she will not be able to change from one to another during employment by the College.  A mandatory payroll deduction of 3% of the salary will be contributed to the employee's retirement fund for persons beginning state service on or after July 27, 1976.
<dt><br>
<dt>Part-time employees are not required to participate in a retirement program.  Such employees wishing to participate are eligible to elect either the TRS program or the ERS program.  Participation in the TIAA-CREF program is available to part-time employees with a term contract.  However, an employee who desires Social Security coverage must first join a retirement system.
<dt><br>
<dt>Each of the three available programs offers certain advantages.  The choice of a retirement program should be made in relation to the employee's particular needs and objectives.</BLOCKQUOTE>
</dl><!-- 0 -->
<dt><br><BR>
<BR>
<B><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="S6B1-5.html">Continue to next section</A></B>
<BR>
<BR>


<CENTER><!-- Graphic Tag --><IMG WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=4  SRC="http://www.potsdam.edu/hr/faculty_handbook/line.blue.GIFF"></CENTER><BR>

