<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>pednine.html - Converted</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="greyone.gif">

<!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=6 COLOR="#290A64"><CENTER>PROJECT OSWEGATCHIE RIVER</CENTER></FONT><P>
<!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=5 COLOR="#290A64"><CENTER>Water Quality Unit<BR>
Lesson Plan 9<BR>
Pedagogy</CENTER></FONT><P>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=5>

<!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#290A64">Phase 1</FONT><BR>
Lesson Activity<BR>
Teacher Behavior<BR>
Student Behavior<P>

<!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#290A64">Phase 2</FONT><BR>
Lesson Activity<BR>
Teacher Behavior<BR>
Student Behavior<P>

<!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=4 COLOR="#290A64">Phase 3</FONT><BR>
Lesson Activity<BR>
Teacher Behavior <BR>
Student Behavior<P>

<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=5><P>


This section is being revised into the above displayed task analysis format.  Please bear with us during this change.  Feel free to look over our thoughts listed below for a full description of our pedagogy according to the New Science Education <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.nap.edu/nap/online/nses/html/3.html">Teaching</A> and<!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.nap.edu/nap/online/nses/html/5.html#as"> Assessment</A> Standards.  Thank you.
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR WIDTH=100% SIZE=5><P>


We continue our examination of pollution and it's effects on our water environments. 
 This activity is of a slower pace then previously seen.  The activity revolves around 
the reading of a story and the students will be writing their own ending to the story. 
 We have been covering pollution regularly so no new introduction is necessary. <P>
 The students should sit on the ground in a semi-circle.  Read the story aloud to 
the students - this is a really good place to interject as much theatrics as possible 
to keep the students attention.  After reading the story out loud, give each student 
a 
copy of the story and have them return to their seats.
Each student will spend time writing an ending to the story they have just heard. 
 After they are finished they should come up with 3 types of aquatic pollution, it 
may be something we have already discussed in class, or they may come up with something 
new.  After everyone is finished writing in their journals, each student should share 
the three types of pollution they came up with.  Each response will be written on 
the board.  Do not duplicate a response if it is already recorded.  The students 
will then brainstorm to come up with two actions they, and their classmates, can do 
to promote 
a clean and healthy environment.  Have the students design a contract they can sign 
that states their intentions in keeping the environment clean.
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
