<html>
<head>
<title> Chapter 6I</title>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<A NAME="VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS"><CENTER><B>VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS</B></CENTER></A>
<br>
<dt><br>
<dt><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6I"><b>I</A>.	GROUP DISABILITY INSURANCE PROGRAM</b>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<A NAME="6J2a"><I>1.</A>	THE PROGRAM</I>
<dt><br>
			<dt>In addition to the disability retirement allowance program described previously all active full-time and active, qualified part- time professional staff members participate in State University's Group Disability Insurance Program administered by TIAA-CREF.  Eligible professional staff members will be covered under this plan on the first day of the month coinciding with or next following completion of one year of service with the State University within the past five years.  This program assures that in the event of total, long-term disability the employee will receive a regular monthly income (as explained in the brochure, "Group Disability Insurance Program for Professional Staff") and premiums will be applied to an annuity during such disability until the employee reaches age 65 or until death, whichever occurs first.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<A NAME="6J2b"><I>2.</A>	ELIGIBILITY FOR COVERAGE</I>
<dt><br>
			<dt>All active full-time and active, qualified part-time professional staff members will be covered under the plan on the first day of the month coinciding with or next following completion of one year of service with State University within the past five years.  If you are absent from work on the day you would otherwise become insured, you will become insured on the date you return to work.
<br><BR>

<dt>If you are rehired within one year from the date employment ceased, you will become eligible for insurance on:
<br><BR>

<dd><dl>
<dt>a.	the date of your re-entry into an eligible class, if you were previously insured under the policy; or
<br><BR>


b.	the date you become eligible for insurance as set forth in "When an Employee Becomes Eligible for Insurance", if you were not previously insured under the policy.  All full months of service in an eligible class prior to the date employment ceased will be used in determining this date.

		</dl>
<dt><br>

<dt><A NAME="6J2c"><I>3.</A>	DEFINITION OF TOTAL DISABILITY</I>
<dt><br>
			<dt>Total disability under this program is the "inability of the employee, by reason of sickness, bodily injury, or pregnancy, to engage in any occupation for which the employee is reasonably fitted by education, training or experience."

		</dl>
<dt><br>

<dt><A NAME="6J2d"><BLOCKQUOTE><I>4.</A>	THE BENEFITS</I>
<dt><br>
			<dt>The plan provides benefits which begin on the first of the month following six consecutive months of total disability and continue during such disability until age 65, or until death, whichever occurs first.  However, if disability commences after the attainment of age 60, benefits are provided until 5 years after the onset of disability or age 70, whichever occurs earlier.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<dt>
			<dt><A NAME="6J2h"><BLOCKQUOTE><I>5.</A>	APPLICATION FOR DISABILITY BENEFITS</I>
<dt><br>
			<dt>Applications are available from the Retirement System or Office of Human Resources.  The application form should be completed and returned to the Office of Human Resources approximately three months after disability begins.</BLOCKQUOTE>
</dl>
	</dl>
<dt>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6J3"><i><BLOCKQUOTE>6</A>.	WORKERS' COMPENSATION</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Workers' Compensation Insurance protects professional staff members who are disabled as a result of an injury arising out of and in the course of their employment.  Benefits include reimbursement of specified medical expenses, scheduled payments for permanent disabilities, and weekly benefits during time lost from the job because of an occupational injury.  All injuries and accidents must be reported to the employee's supervisor.  The supervisor must file a report with the College's Office of Public Safety.</BLOCKQUOTE>

	</dl>
<dt>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6J4"><i><BLOCKQUOTE>7</A>.	SOCIAL SECURITY</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>The U.S. Social Security Administration protects professional staff members who are disabled and who have paid into the system.  Details are available from the local Social Security Office located in Ogdensburg, New York.</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<BR>


