<P>

<html>
<head>
<title> Chapter 6: Retirement, Disability and Death Benefits</title>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#0000ff" vlink="#ff00ff">

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=462 HEIGHT=87  SRC="../FACBOOK.GIF"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS"><CENTER><B>VI.  RETIREMENT, DISABILITY AND DEATH BENEFITS</B></CENTER></A>

<br><br>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B"><b>B</A>.	NEW YORK STATE TEACHERS' RETIREMENT SYSTEM (TRS)</b>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><i><A NAME="6B1">1</A>.	THE SYSTEM</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>The present System was established in 1921 to administer the funds from which New York State public school teachers, outside New York City, receive retirement benefits. The System is regulated by law.   Operation is under the direction of a 10-member retirement board and is reviewed by the State Insurance Department.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B2"><i>2</A>.	MEMBERSHIP</i>
<dt><br>
		<dt>Membership is mandatory and automatic for all full-time New York State public school teachers, outside New York City, except those employed under the Comprehensive Employment and Training Act (CETA).
<dt><br>
<dt>Membership for teachers employed less than full time is optional.
<dt><br>
<dt>Eligible employees of the State University of New York and the State Education Department have the option of joining the system.

	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3"><i>3</A>.	DEFINITIONS</i>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3a">a</A>)	Tier I Members - members who last joined the System prior to July 1, 1973.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3b">b</A>)	Tier II Members - members who last joined the System during the period July 1, 1973 through July 26, 1976.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3c">c</A>)	Tier III Members - members who last joined the System during the period July 27, 1976 through August 31, 1983.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3d">d</A>)	Tier IV Members - members who last joined NYSTRS on or after September 1, 1983.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3e">e</A>)	Retirement Allowance - the total amount paid the retired member each year.  The retirement allowance is paid in 12 equal monthly installments.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3f">f</A>)	Pension - that portion of the retirement allowance funded by employer contributions.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3g">g</A>)	Annuity - that portion of the retirement allowance funded by member contributions, if any.
</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3h">h</A>)	Final Average Salary (FAS)

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3hi">i)	3-Year FAS - the average of a member's three highest consecutive years of regular salary, excluding termination pay, retirement bonuses, pay for unused sick days or accumulated vacation, and increases in regular compensation exceeding 20%.

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3hii">i</A>i)	5-Years FAS - the average of a member's five highest      consecutive years of salary without the limitations of the 3-year FAS.  The 5-year FAS generally applies only to those members whose last date of membership is prior to June 17, 1971.  The 5-year FAS is used when it is greater than the 3-year FAS.
</dl>
		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3i">i</A>)	Prior Service - creditable service rendered before a member's date of membership.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B3j">j</A>)	Transfer - the carrying over of service presently credited in one New York State public retirement system to another, along with the monetary reserves accumulated to fund the benefits.
</dl>
	</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4"><i>4</A>.	RETIREMENT PLAN FOR TIER I MEMBERS (PRE 7/1/73) THE CAREER RETIREMENT PLAN</i>
<dt><br>
<dt>The benefits for Tier I members which are outlined below are those provided under the Career Retirement Plan.  Members who joined the Retirement System prior to July 1, 1970 may also be eligible for benefits computed under the Non-Contributory Plan, which will be paid if this plan provides a greater benefit.  To be eligible for the Non-Contributory Plan, a member must be in service at age 55 or older and credited with a combination of at least 20 years of NYS and out-of-State service, or be age 65 or older (with less than 20 years credit) and in full-time service throughout the two semesters immediately preceding age 65 or any two consecutive semesters thereafter.

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4a">a</A>)	Service Retirement Eligibility

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4ai">i</A>)	Thirty-five years of total credited service at any age or,

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4aii">ii</A>)	Age 55 or older with the equivalent of 10 or more years of credited full-time NYS service, at least two of which must have been rendered since June 30, 1967 and since last becoming a member, or

			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4aiii">iii</A>)	Age 55 or older with the equivalent of two or more years of credited full-time NYS service, at least two of which must have been rendered since June 30, 1967, since age 53, and since last becoming a member.
</dl>
		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4b">b</A>)	Allowance Calculation

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4bi">i</A>)	The pension of a member credited with the equivalent of at least 20 years of full-time NYS service is calculated under a formula of 2% of final average salary (FAS) for each year of State service since July 1, 1959, 1.8% of FAS for each year of NYS service prior to that date, and 1% of FAS for each year of credited out-of-State service.  Credited out- of-State service is used in the computation only up to a maximum of 35 years of total service.
<dt><br>
				<dt>The maximum pension payable is 75% of FAS.
<dt><br>
				<dt>Members who have made contributions to the System receive an annuity in addition to the pension.
			</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4bii">ii</A>)	For members eligible to retire having fewer than the equivalent of 20 years of full-time NYS service, the pension is computed as above but with a 5% reduction for each year of State service under 20 years.  For example, with 15 years of NYS service, the actual pension is 75% of the pension computed under the Tier I formula; with 12 years, 60%; with 19 years, 95%.  The minimum pension payable under the computation for fewer than 20 years of NYS service is 50% of the Tier I calculation.
</dl>
		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4c">c)	Disability Retirement
<dt><br>
			<dt>A member under age 55 may qualify for a disability retirement allowance under Tier I after being credited with 10 years of full-time NYS service, at least two of which have been rendered since June 30, 1967 and since (s)he last joined the System, if permanently physically and/or mentally incapacitated from further teaching service and (s)he ceased teaching because of the disability.
<dt><br>
<dt>As a general rule, a member under age 55 retiring for disability can expect to receive a minimum pension of approximately 1/3 of FAS, plus an annuity from her or his contributions, if any.
<dt><br>
<dt>Members over age 55 who meet the eligibility requirements for disability retirement will have their allowances computed on the same basis as a service retirement allowance.
<dt><br>
<dt>In order to qualify for a disability retirement allowance, the member's disability must be affirmed by the System's Medical and Retirement Boards.  A member who becomes disabled should request information from the System concerning the amount of the disability payments and the procedures to be followed to effect a disability retirement.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4d">d)	Deferred Retirement (Vesting)
<dt><br>
			<dt>Under Tier I, a member credited with the equivalent of 10 years of full-time NYS service, at least two of which were rendered since June 30, 1967 and since last becoming a member, who discontinues service on or after June 30, 1970 will have membership continued unless (s)he withdraws from the System.  All benefits are forfeited by withdrawal from membership.  If the member does not withdraw, (s)he will be vested automatically.  Once vested, the member will qualify for a deferred retirement allowance at age 55, but (s)he still must file an application for deferred retirement at least 30 but not more than 90 days before the date of retirement.
<dt><br>
<dt>The deferred retirement allowance is computed exactly the same as the Tier I service retirement allowance, that is, a Tier I pension for the equivalent of 20 or more years of full-time NYS service, or a reduced pension for fewer than 20 years of such  service.  If a member ceased teaching before June 30, 1976, the factor used for years of credited NYS service rendered before July 1, 1959 is 1.2% instead of 1.8%.
<dt><br>
<dt>As with all other allowances, an annuity based on the member's own contributions, if any, is paid in addition to the pension.
<dt><br>
<dt>A member who ceased teaching prior to June 30, 1970 credited with at least 10 years of full-time NYS service may be eligible for a deferred allowance under an earlier law.  The member should communicate with the System for information.                 

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4e">e)	Annuity Contributions
<dt><br>
			<dt>Members who have contributed to the System receive an annuity (in addition to the pension) as part of the retirement allowance.
<dt><br>
<dt>Members who joined the System July 1, 1970 through July 26, 1976 can only contribute to the System for the purchase of allowable prior service or military service credit.
<dt><br>
<dt>Pre-7/1/70 members who are still contributing through payroll deduction may discontinue such contributions at any time.  However, once having discontinued, these members may not resume making contributions through payroll deduction.
<dt><br>
<dt>A member who last joined before July 1, 1970 may voluntarily deposit directly with the System, once each year, up to 4% of her or his earnable salary for the preceding school year for the purchase of additional annuity at retirement.  These deposits currently earn interest of 5%, the same as regular contributions.  It is also possible, at the time of retirement, for such a member to make a single payment for the purchase of additional annuity, in an amount sufficient to bring the maximum retirement allowance up to not more than one-half of final average salary.
<dt><br>
<dt>As of January 1, 1988, Tier I and Tier II members may at the time of retirement withdraw contributions made toward the purchase of annuities.  The application for withdrawal of contributions must be filed no earlier than the date the member files her/his application for retirement and no later than the day preceding the effective date of retirement.  The taxable portion of any such refund is reportable as ordinary income for Federal Income tax purposes in the year the payment is made. If a member has made Special Service (age 55 retirement) contributions, these contributions may be withdrawn at any time before retirement with possible tax consequences.  Default on a loan at retirement reduces the member's annuity contributions by the outstanding balance of the loan.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B4f">f)	Part-Time Service</a>
<dt><br>
			<dt>In computing benefits and meeting eligibility requirements under Tier I, part-time service in the same school year is credited according to the following schedule of full days.
<br>
<center>
<table width=70%>
<tr>
<th>DAYS/YR</th> <th>CREDIT</th> <th>DAYS/YR</th> <th>CREDIT</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Under 20</td><td>None</td> <td>90-109</td><td>5 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>        
<td>20-29</td> <td>1 month</td> <td>110-129</td> <td>6 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>30-49</td> <td>2 months</td> <td>130-149</td><td> 7 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>50-69 </td><td>3 months</td> <td>150-169</td> <td>8 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>70-89</td>  <td>4 months</td><td>170 +</td> <td>1 year</td>
</tr>
</table>
</center> 

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dt><i><A NAME="6B5">5</A>.	RETIREMENT PLAN FOR TIER II MEMBERS (7/1/73 - 7/26/76)</i>

<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B5a">a</A>)	Service Retirement Eligibility
<dt><br>
			<dd>i)	Age 55 or older with the equivalent of 10 or more years of credited full-time NYS service, five of which must have been rendered since the last date of membership, or
<dt><br>
			<dd>ii)	Age 55 or older with the equivalent of five years of credited full-time service rendered since the last date of membership, provided two have been rendered since the 53rd birthday.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B5b">b</A>)	Allowance Calculation
<dt><br>
			<dt>This allowance is computed under the Tier I formula described above; i.e., 2% of FAS for each year of credited NYS service rendered since July 1, 1959, etc.  A maximum allowance of 75% of FAS is possible.  The regular Tier I reduction applies when credited NYS service totals less than 20 years.
<dt><br>
<dt>An additional reduction is imposed under Tier II when retirement occurs before age 62 with less than 30 years of NYS service.  The reduced benefit is computed as follows:
<br>
<center>
<table width=70%>
<tr>
                      <th align=left>AGE</th>                  <th align=left>% OF TIER I BENEFIT</th>
</tr>

                      <tr><td>61</td>                           <td>94%</td></tr>
                       <tr><td>60</td>                           <td>88%</td></tr>
                       <tr><td>59</td>                           <td>85%</td></tr>
                       <tr><td>58</td>                           <td>82%</td></tr>
                       <tr><td>57</td>                           <td>79%</td></tr>
                       <tr><td>56</td>                           <td>76%</td></tr>
                       <tr><td>55</td>                           <td>73%</td></tr>
</table>
</center>
<dt><br>
<dt>The pension for retirement at age 62 or older when credited with less than 20 years of State service is reduced only by Tier I reduction.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B5c">c</A>)	Disability Retirement
<dt><br>
			<dt>The requirements are the same as for Tier I disability, except that at least five of the 10 years must have been rendered since last becoming a member.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B5d">d</A>)	Deferred Retirement (Vesting)
<dt><br>
			<dt>The eligibility requirements are the same as for Tier I vesting with the additional requirement that at least five years must have been rendered since last becoming a member.  Calculation of allowance is the same as for service retirement under Tier I.

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B5e">e</A>)	Annuity Contributions
<dt><br>
			<dt>Details are given under Tier I, section 4(e).

		</dl>
<dt><br>
<dd><dl>
<dt><A NAME="6B5f">f</A>)	Part-Time Service
<dt><br>
			<dt>In computing benefits and meeting eligibility requirements under Tier II, part-time service is credited the same as for Tier I.

		</dl>
<dt><BR>
<BR>
<B><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="S1C.html">Continue to next section</A></B>
<BR>
<BR>


