<BODY>
Journal entry 9/8/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
I really enjoyed our first day with the Gouverneur students.  They seemed interested 
in being at SUNY but maybe overwhelmed.  It is only their second day of school.  
We played a name game with them to get to know each other.  The most interesting 
part for me was how they laughed at each other when someone said something silly.  They never 
forgot the silly thing however.  It probably would have gone even better had it not 
been 90oF and sunny.  It was so hot!  <BR>
We took them inside and split them into 2 groups.  Eric and I went over topography 
maps and general river characteristics.  Both groups seemed quite interested.  I 
know this because they remembered and answered questions on the pretest questionnaire 
correctly.  <BR>
I think we're off to a good start.  I believe Eric and I are working well together. 
 Mike said that I held the students attention and had a good strong voice with them. 
  Probably a good thing as most are taller than me!  I asked him to keep the comments 
coming even if they're negative.  <BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="staceytw.html">Journal 2</A></H4>
<BR>

</BODY>
</HTML>
