<BODY>
Tyna L. Heise<BR>
GRED571<BR>
Journal<BR>
<BR>
September 6, 1996<BR>
Today was the first day I met my students, Stacey, Eric, Rita, and Melissa all met 
the kids for the first time yesterday.  Stacey, Eric, Rita and myself all have class 
together Thursday nights so I talked to all of them about today's plan.  The others 
had a played a name game with the students and Stacey filled me in on all the "names" 
they had chosen.  When I introduced myself I did so in spirit of the game.  I was 
very surprised how affronted the students were at the prospect of having to repeat 
the game!  I assured them they would have to do no such thing and had them introduce themselves 
to me so I could place names to faces.   I warned them that I had little spies and 
I knew what names they had chosen the day before - I had memorized them, but my nerves had all the names flying right out of my head and I was forced to examine my cheat 
sheet on almost every name.  We had a good time as they went through their introductions 
then we moved on to the first or    der of business.<BR>
Friday's are going to be assessment days, and I needed the students to decide how 
they wanted to proceed with the assessment process.  I felt that I would have more 
of their cooperation if THEY had a hand in the decision-making process.  They class 
wanted to do worksheets and present the material on the worksheets - the two subgroups would 
work on different worksheets according to their biology or chemistry subgroup and 
present the material to  the other subgroup.  This would allow each student, no matter 
which subgroup they were in, a chance to learn all that we were teaching.  The students 
wanted to play a game as review; they requested we play a game every week or every 
other week, I bargained them to every third week, and I must admit I am looking forward to that every third week as much as they are!  Basically we just covered what my  were and what they could expect in the week to come. <BR><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="tynatwo.html">journal 2</A>

</BODY>
</HTML>
