<BODY>
Journal entry 9/18/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Class went well.  This was our first field trip and we went to Cranberry Lake. The 
students seemed interested.   Brandon and Erica were constantly volunteering to perform 
the water tests.  I loved it.<BR>
We only got 55 minutes with the students and didn't get nearly as much accomplished 
as we would have liked.  However, what we did accomplish was great.   As far as time 
goes, I'm going to concentrate of quality and in depth understanding.<BR>
By the next river visit, I'll have nutrient agar plates to take with me so that the 
students can spread for fecal coliforms at the sites.  That should help them understand 
the process better.  It's hard to explain something if they don't have prior knowledge, especially in science.<BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="staceyfo.html">Journal 4</A></H4>

</BODY>
