<HEAD>
<TITLE>tynathree.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
September 18, 1996<BR>
Our first day on the river - wow - what a difference in those students when they get 
outside and start doing activities they are excited about.  Stacey and I were in 
charge of data for five of the tests but first things first.  We had all the kids 
sit down together and write in their journals basic information about the si    te and the 
weather conditions - basically we are looking to instill good scientific data keeping. 
 Each group had been divided into jobs, we reminded them of these jobs and got started.  The kids worked fantastic together.  We didn't really emphasize the jobs in the 
group setting, but the was no need.  The was no need for a reminder to get on task, 
the kids congratulated themselves through camaraderie - again eliminating that job 
necessity.  The recorder was the only job that was official and we all helped to make certain 
that the right information was going into the notebook.  Basically, today was a huge 
blue ribbon day!<BR>
<!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="tynafour.html"><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#084842">Journal 4 </A> </BODY>
</HTML>
