<HEAD>
<TITLE>staceyfo.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Journal entry 9/19/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<BR>
<BR>
Today class went very well.  We worked through our calculations of test data quickly. 
 Kate, Brandon, Erica and Charity all worked on determining Q-values and conversion 
factors.  I had to push 2 students to stay involved as they were quiet and somewhat 
distant.  The pushing seemed to do the trick today.  We discussed how we would be doing 
the coliform testing and they decided that they would like to take the BOD measurements 
on Monday instead of me.  I was happy because I think that shows great interest in the project.<BR>
We discussed that their journals would be placed on the Web as would their photos. 
 We agreed that if someone didn't like their picture that we wouldn't use it.  I 
like that rule!<BR>
Sharing our data went well and by next week (BOD can't be read for 5 days), we'll 
complete this weeks form, make copies for everyone and get results up on the Web.<BR>
We finished the day playing Heavy Metals Tic Tac Toe.  The game went extremely well. 
 Each student was eager to participate.   They worked well as a team and showed energy, 
enthusiasm, research skills (looked through reference material quickly and accurately) and consistent thought processes.   Brandon, Erica and Charity won 2 games to 
1. <BR>
Eric and I took them to the Student Union for a few minutes before they left.  They 
love going there.  <BR>
Everyday I feel more comfortable with them.  They are great kids and maybe teaching 
junior high isn't as bad as most people say.  We had a blast today!<BR>
<H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="staceyfi.html">Journal 5</A></H4>
