<BODY>
Journal entry 9/26/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<BR>
<BR>
Testing went twice as fast today at Fine.  We even spread our fecal coliform plates. 
 Unfortunately the batteries were dead in our TDS tester though.  <BR>
We had a visitor in our group today from one of Mike's other science classes.  Nice 
addition.  She helped out a lot.  Enjoyed having her.<BR>
For the last 20 minutes, we went exploring near a set of rapids.  Brandon was the 
trailblazer and he was excellent.  I bet he's had a lot of experience in the woods. 
 Erica, Kate and Charity seemed to enjoy our exploring.  So did I.  We found a tree 
that a beaver had recently cut down.<BR>
I hope the students are happy with what they're learning and that they see some relevance. 
 I worry that we don't have the time to do the "best" job.  Even so, I'm hoping that 
the administration will be pleased when they see the deep understanding of concepts the student will have soon.<BR><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="staceysi.html"><H4 ALIGN=CENTER>Journal 6</H4></A>

