<BODY>
September 25, 1996<BR>
RIVER SITE!  These days are just plain fun for me and the students.  I felt as if 
I had a bit more confidence this week and I tried to become even more involved in 
helping the students perform the tests while trying to ensue that they all did something. 
 I have noticed some small cliches within our group of four, and I deliberately attempted 
to split the cliches up while encouraging those students to work with others in the 
group they might not regularly have worked with.  This week was the same as last 
week in that the students really worked hard to perform the tasks given to the best 
of their ability and in a very timely fashion.  Stacey had wanted to have them get back in their groups and begin to really work on calculating out the q-factors, however we decided to let them have some fun hiking time 
because Mrs. French had located some rapids along the bank a bit down-stream. 
 Mrs. French had pointed them out to me, and I knew that the students enjoyed looking 
at the ecosystem as much as they did testing the water, and I felt they deserved to 
do both since they had worked so well together to get all the tests performed not 
once but twice in different positions on the river.<BR>
I should have been more wary to speak with Stacey about my suggestion before offering 
the suggestion to the students.  I allowed my excitement of some fun time with them 
to get me carried away - another error - another lesson learned!  <BR>
<BR>
