<BODY>
Journal entry 9/29/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<BR>
<BR>
Spent time tonight reorganizing task analysis pages for the Web and working on the 
journal home page.<BR>
I'm not sure how I like going to the river 4 weeks in a row.  I think it's hard for 
the students to stay focused on Thursdays because the major focus is calculations 
and discussion of test results.  Originally we planned on river visits every other 
week which would have allowed us to incorporate lessons relating to the parameters we are 
testing.  I think they need more practical working knowledge of the parameters for 
the most effective learning to occur.  <BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="staceyse.html">Journal 7</A></H4>

</BODY>
