<BODY>
Journal entry 10/1/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<BR>
<BR>
Booked the Kellas MAC lab for Thursday.  Going to have the students surf the Net. That should be fun for them and me.  I want them to find at least 2 articles or sites related to what we are doing: water quality testing of a river. As a result of the many schedule and lesson changes, I'm feeling disoriented.  I want to make sure the students 
don't feel that way too.  I think this activity will help emphasize why we have taken all that data at the 4 sites and why it's so important to me, the schools, their communities and them personally.  I want them to also see that their project is interesting to many other people around the country.  I'll show them where our home page is and 
how many links we have to organizations interested in what we're doing.  I surfed the Net tonight and found 2 similar projects that I didn't know about.  Time permitting, I also want them to take a Virtual Reality Tour of the Los Angeles river that I found.  I'm interested in seeing if doing a similar project for the Oswegatchie River would be possible in the future.<BR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="staceyei.html">Journal 8</A></H4>

