<BODY>
October 2, 1996<BR>
River Site!!  We performed two sites in this one day.  Our first site was at the cemetery 
in Gouverneur and the second at Richville.  At both sit   &oslash;es the kids performed 
fantastically.  They were right on top of the tests and the results for that matter.  Stacey and I altered a few things this time around.  Because time was of the essence, 
we split the team up into two groups of two and split ourselves up to handle them. 
 We switched tests at the second site so that the students still got to perform all 
the tests that day.  We had some time left over, but, because we played last week we didn't let the loose this week, instead we got them started 
on the calculations for the test results we did have to save them some time for tomorrow.  The river weeks are so easy, and the fresh air seems to be so great for the 
kids!<BR>
