<BODY>
Journal entry 10/3/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<BR>
<BR>
Eric called in sick today.  I found out when I got to class.  I missed the call he'd left at my office.  I was a little nervous at first since we had always taught together but then I decided that it was time for me to teach alone.  It would be good for me.  I've done it on the college level and I could do this too!<BR>
We went to Stowell.  I wanted them to see where we keep the fecal coliform plates. Gina, Charity, Steven and Brandon each counted colonies on plates.  We took 4 yesterday. Their spreading techniques are improving.   The colonies were much more uniformly distributed.  We did have 1 plate with fungus however.  <BR>
We calculated Q-values and results.  They had to write the preliminary water quality index for Gouverneur and Richville in the journals.<BR>
Then we were off the the Kellas MAC lab.  Our main activity was the Net Search of anything related to our project.  I was interested to see what areas they would research. Charity searched fecal coliforms, E.coli and bacteria.  She found some cool stuff but it may not be useful to our project.  She worked well and seemed to enjoy herself. 
 Brandon likes computers.  He has one at home.  He searched chemicals in rivers. He didn't have much luck but tried hard.  Even though he wanted to play games, he persevered through his assignment.   I was proud of him.    Steven had similar problems finding relevant information on his search but he did find a real interesting site 
on testing.  Jennifer is quick, pleasant and a joy.  She found a site early.  I have the address.  Andy did a great job also.  He found a testing site early in the period.  Kate found some interesting letters from people involved in water testing.  Gina wanted to search water pollution.  She didn't have much luck.  We had trouble connecting 
to some sites. <BR>
We closed the lesson with a journal write.  They needed to write at least 2 paragraphs about: did they like or dislike working on the Net and what site and/or address did they find.  Why is that site/address relevant to our project.<P>


<!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="Stacey104.html">Journal 9</A>




