<TITLE>tynaeight.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
October 4, 1996<BR>
Wow, today's lesson just left me feeling so fantastic!  The lesson today revolved 
around the kids portraying members of the community (roles which I assigned) to convince 
the council (myself &amp; Mrs. French) whether we should build a d    am in our little 
town or not.  The kids were just supposed to come up with ideas or statements that 
would help them identify their arguments.  They had a really hard time with that 
and I began to get a bit worried.  It wasn't that the students didn't understand 
what I wanted them to do, they simply didn't find it all that interesting.  I was beginning to 
get a bit upset, but it wasn't that they found it uninteresting as an activity, just 
they didn't like the option of writing out statements.  The students asked me if 
they could draw pictures of their ideas instead, and to put it mildly, I jumped on the idea. 
 I encouraged them to use all their creativity with one hitch, they had to describe 
in detail all the ideas they were trying to encompass with this one drawing.  They 
loved it, and drew some fantastic pictures (see the student journals for chemistry!)<BR>
Some of the students aren't as comfortable speaking in front of their peers.  I noticed 
particularly today during their role playing.  I asked questions to     try to draw 
them out a bit, and that helped.  I just cross my fingers and hope that these kids 
will recognize all the potential that I see so easily!<BR>
I really made my first major conversational error today as well.  Miss. Fobare and 
I were playing dodge ball with the kids after they finished their work.  The kids 
weren't really aiming for me until they had to hit me in order to get some of their 
players back.  Well, I bumbled the ball and lost it, getting out, and without thinking (OBVIOUSLY) 
said "Oh, SHI    T!".  The students jumped on this immediately and chastised me thoroughly. 
 Talk about feeling completely humbled!  The students are becoming more and more comfortable around me, and I love to see them opening up to me!<BR><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="tynanine.html"><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#084842">Journal 9</A>
<BR>

</BODY>
