<BODY>
Journal 10/4/96<BR>
Stacey Maguire<P>


Eric, Tyna and I agreed on how to tackle the midterm.  We are going to have a written part and a lab practical.  We are asking Mike to copy relevant chapters from our water test book and give them to the students.  We are making study guides to go with those copies.  We hope this will help them.  I feel bad that we don't have a text they 
can take home.  It's such a good book.  Eric and I will make up lab practicals for each group.  Tyna will administer the midterm (both sections) at Gouverneur.<P>


Saw Kate swim 2 of her 3 races today at Canton.  She has great potential.  She introduced me to Stacey and Angela who will be joining us on our river visit to Ogdensburg.<P>


Kate suggested a crossword puzzle format for a homework assignment.  I'm going to see what I can do about it. <P>


I met with Eric this morning.  I liked his rubric for field work very much.  I also liked the way he did the grade ranges.  I want to use his format.  He liked the way Tyna and I rescheduled some lessons.  So we are a go!<P>

