<BODY>
October 7, 1996<BR>
Todays activity revolves around artwork directly.  Last week, with Mr. Toth, the students learned about maps.  To take off from that directly, I had the stduents draw out sections of the Oswegatchie River on poster boards.  I will be turning the poster boards into a board game board later on so that we can use it for review of the final. The kids really got into this activity!  More than anything they love to be doing 
something which allows them to use creativity!<BR>
To continue about my OOPS! last week, the kids wanted me to pla    y dodge ball again today, but I was steel feeling pretty bad about last week, AND the kids had been picking on me all day about my blunder.  One of the kids came up with the perfect solution!  Two of my students wanted me to be immediately forgiven, after all, everyone makes mistakes.  I told them that wasn't fair - I expected them to abide the rules that I broke, and I should be punished as well.  They decided that a fair punishment was for me to sit out of dodge ball for 10 minutes.  I was also to be very careful about what I said- they would be keeping an eye on me!  I felt it was fantastic the way the decided my punishment based on the exact methods we use to punish them!  Today 
was again a great day!<BR><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="tynaten.html"><!-- Font Tag --><FONT COLOR="#084842">Journal 10</A>

