<HEAD>
<TITLE>Tyna1021.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
October 21, 1996<BR>
<BR>
I performed an activity known as "Alice in Waterland" with the kids today.  The best part was their focus on the story and using their imagination.  I read a bit of dialogue to them while they had their eyes closed to help them envision the local water cycle - to their house, through their house, and out of their house into the original source.  Then the kids drew pictures of their individual houses and water cycles, listing chemicals that affect the water and the habitat that feeds off of this water. 
 <BR>
As usual, when given something very creative to do, they went to town and did fabulous jobs!<P>

