<BODY>
Journal 10/14<BR>
Stacey Maguire<BR>
<BR>
I must catch my journal up.  Boy!   It's been so busy lately.<P>
<B>Wednesday</B><BR>

Our trip to Odgensburg.  Mike brought 6 students from other science classes with him.  They were a great addition.  They listened well and offered many answers and suggestions.  <BR>
Erica was back.  I told her I missed her.  The group worked well and seemed interested in what they were doing.<BR>
The day ened with me, Rita, Mike and many of the students paying tag.  That was fun. Think the students enjoyed.  I did!<P>


<B>Thursday </B><P>


Eric and I had each group calculate Q-values and test results.  Our main objective for the day was to review with them for the midterm on Friday.  I made a Jeopardy game which I thought  they would really like.   Going by the actual Jeopardy rules didn't turn out to be good.  Some students didn't like the fact that if a group answered a question right they got to go again.  In general, the students were just wild 
from then on out except Jen and Kate.  There were many negative comments made about the class and other classmates.  I could feel my temper rising but we didn't acknowledge much of their outbursts until near the end of class.  Noone went to the Union.  I don't think Eric and I ever denied them going before.  Just before we let them go to catch 
the bus, I told them that we were very disappointed in most of them.  I wanted them to know that we love having them come to SUNY and that we like them all very much.  But...it makes us sad when they act the way they did today and that thewhole class was treated the same (no Union for anyone) even though not all were acting up.  I told them 
the reason we wanted to review with them was that we wanted them all to pass the midterm and that we believed they were all very capable of getting A's.<BR>



Eric and I made up the midterm exam practical during the afternoon and gave them to Tyna during our team meeting that night.<P>


<B>Friday</B><P>


I did a great amount of Web work today.  Feels great.  Wow has this project gotten huge.  Sometimes there are just not enough hours in the day to get everything done! I left a message for Dr. Doody to drop in the Chem folder.<P>

